title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix beef lightly with 3/4 cup cheese, egg, crumbs, onion and seasonings until well blended.
Shape into loaf in a shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off drippings.
Pour tomato sauce over loaf.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: gail's lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except lime sherbet. Be sure to chill pineapple juice and possibly jello and water mixture several hours before serving time so it will be cold. Pour into punch bowl and float lime sherbet on top.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cut potatoes into small chunks and cook in salted water.
Clean dandelions, selected bleached, tender stalks.
Cut in short lengths and add to cooked potatoes (do not drain).
Add vinegar and bacon fat to taste.
Endive can be fixed with potatoes the same way. Delicious.

title: foil grill spuds
directions: Cut butter or margarine into 1 tablespoon patties.
Spread layers of potatoes, onion and butter.
Sprinkle each layer with Lawry's on heavy-duty aluminum foil, which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Wrap tightly, sealing all edges.
Place on grill, turning every 1/2 hour for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: popovers
directions: Combine flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a well in center of flour and add eggs, butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fill well greased 5 ounce custard cups or muffin pans half full.
Bake in a hot 400° oven until brown and crisp.
Makes 8 Popovers.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into cakes and brown in butter.

title: rosella
directions: Take an iron skillet and fry 2 strips of bacon until brittle. Add fresh vegetables to bacon grease and add 2 tablespoons corn, 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until vegetables are tender.
Very good with everything.

title: fruited trifle
directions: Arrange 1/2 of pound cake in bottom of serving bowl, cutting to fit.
Brush with Frangelico.
Pour on 1/2 of Custard Sauce. Arrange fruit (1/2 of each kind) on top of custard.
Repeat process.
Whip cream with sugar until thick.
Spread on top. Garnish with fruit.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients with meat.
Put layer of flour tortillas, layer of meat, layer of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and place in hot oven until melted.

title: sharon's bean dip
directions: Layer refried beans, sour cream, lettuce and tomatoes.
Top with taco sauce, if desired.
Great with tortilla chips!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese in electric mixer.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix again.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour, butter and sour cream.
Mix well and pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Shut oven off and let cool 2 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: shepherd's pie(yields 4 servings)
directions: Cook meat, onion and carrot slowly until meat is done and onion is transparent.
(Do not brown.)
Drain off all liquid; add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart baking dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are browned.

title: molasses cake
directions: Bake at 325° to 350° until done.
Check with a toothpick.

title: honey peanut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix shortening, peanut butter and honey. Add eggs; mix well.

title: oysters in patty shells
directions: Place oysters in a saucepan; cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until edges of oysters begin to curl.
Drain.
Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion and saute until tender.
Add flour, stirring until blended.
Stir in next 6 ingredients and oysters.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Spoon oyster mixture into patty shells, and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ginger carrots(diabetic)
directions: Rinse, trim and peel carrots. Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Steam 15 to 20 minutes or until barely tender.

title: fried sugar tortillas bunuelos
directions: In saucepan, heat milk and butter to boiling.
Cool.
Stir in eggs.
Stir dry ingredients in.
Shape into balls.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Fry in deep fat 4 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar or dip in syrup.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix first nine ingredients.
Spread 1 tablespoon mixture on each slice of ham.
Roll each slice like a jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and freeze.
When ready to serve, cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Let thaw 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Put cherry pie filling in blender and puree.
Partially cool cake and cut up.
Stir together with pie filling.
Put into jello mold or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and chill.

title: irish stew
directions: In a heavy pan, cover the bottom with oil. Roll stew meat in flour after adding salt, pepper and garlic salt. Brown the floured meat on all sides, then add water.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until the meat is tender.
Add vegetables and cook until they are done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Bake frozen pie shells according to package directions.
Allow to cool.
Mix lemon juice and condensed milk, then add fruit and Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour into the prepared pie shells and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium; stir in remaining flour.
Heat oil to 375°.
Roll dough on floured board to 3/8 inch thick.
Cut and put into hot oil.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes until brown on both sides.
Do not prick; drain.
Serve plain or sugared or frosted.
Makes 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Chill
and	serve.	This is sooo good on a hot summer day.
I have substituted a zucchini for the avocado and results are just as good to me.

title: corn chowder
directions: Simmer onion and potatoes in small amount of water until mushy.
Do not drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add oleo, cheese, corn and half and half to potato mixture.
Crumble cooked bacon on top.
Cook slowly for 1 hour or longer.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli in boiling water just long enough to thaw. Remove from water and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Put chicken on top of broccoli and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese, lemon juice, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: frankie's fish with swiss cheese
directions: Saute onion in butter until done.
Poach fish in milk until done.
Layer fish in ovenproof dish.
Spread onions over fillets evenly.
Lay slices of cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Brown under broiler.

title: cheesy steak strips
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Brown meat in butter.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Continue to cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Mix soup, cream cheese, broth, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: front porch lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon juice and cold water; mix well.
Chill and serve over ice.
Yields 7 1/4 cups.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Chill dough.
Roll 1/8-inch thick and cut into desired shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These crispy cookies are delicious.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, egg yolks, salt and juice and cook until thickened (use Mandarin orange juice and pineapple juice).
Cook 1/2 box pasta for 7 minutes; drain.
Add cooled pasta to cooled sauce; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add drained pineapple and Mandarin oranges, little of a half of marshmallows and large Cool Whip; refrigerate again until used.

title: marni's chicken and vegetable couscous
directions: In a large saute pan, saute the onions and garlic in olive oil until brown.
Remove onion mixture temporarily, then saute the chicken until brown.
Return onions to pan.
Add tomatoes, curry powder, cayenne, cinnamon, honey, vermouth and broth.

title: aunt bessie's power pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This is good for constipation and keeping you regular.
Only eat 1/4 cup in morning as a rule. May increase amount to 1/2 cup 3 times a day if needed.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups of batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 15 minutes.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and butter.
Remove from heat; add milk.
Mix well.
Spread caramel over cake.
Spread remaining cake mix over caramel.
Top with nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Arrange in greased baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well; drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(I have found that cake mixes with pudding do not work as well.)

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers thin.
Soak cucumbers and onions 3 hours in salt and water to cover.
Drain well.
Boil sugar, vinegar, spices and celery which has been cut in 2-inch pieces.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Let get hot, but don't boil.
Seal in jars and turn upside-down.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix together sugar and vegetable oil; cream together.
Add apple slices, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and eggs.
Cream.
Add flour.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased pan) and bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Boil until a drop forms
a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
You can use more or fewer dates according to taste and may add or substitute coconut for nuts.
Thoroughly wet a cloth and lay on counter.
Pour the candy into a roll shape on the cloth and roll up in the cloth.
Let sit overnight or until hard and cloth is dry.
Unroll and slice.

title: cheryl's mandarin orange cake
directions: Blend ingredients. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool completely.

title: butter crunch candy
directions: In large heavy pan, cook over medium heat first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly until a teaspoon of syrup in cold water forms a brittle mass (285°).
At end of cooking time syrup will be thick and amber color.
Be careful not to scorch.
Keep heat low.
Pour at once into jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Spread evenly. Cool 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle with grated milk chocolate (5 ounce bar) in even layer.
When heat has melted chocolate spread, then pat and sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts in even layer.
Break into pieces.
Makes 2 pounds of crunch.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Combine sugars, shortening and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices.
Gradually add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes on high speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Top with Butter Rum Sauce.

title: flaky apple turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate biscuits and press and roll each one into 4-inch circles.
Mix all seasonings and sugar together. Spoon 2 tablespoons of apples into the center of each biscuit. Spoon 1 teaspoon of sugar mixture over apples.
Fold dough in half.
Press edges together with fork to seal.
Dip both sides in margarine then into remaining sugar mixture.
Place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remove and cool.
Makes 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Completely grease a Tube or Bundt pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
With kitchen shears cut each biscuit into 4 pieces, roll each piece in the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Place into the prepared tube or bundt pan.
Melt butter or margarine in a sauce pan, add brown sugar and the rest of cinnamon sugar mixture to the sauce pan.
Pour over top of the biscuit pieces in the tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 - 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes.
Invert onto a serving dish and enjoy.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine chicken, celery, onion, nuts, pasta, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise with water and soup; add to the mixture and gently stir in hard cooked eggs.
Turn mixture into greased 9 X 13 pan or casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Note: If you wish this can be made earlier and refrigerated.
When doing so add 10-15 minutes to baking time.

title: three alarm chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, garlic and chili mix.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain beans and discard liquid.
Drain jalapenos; reserve liquid.
Remove stems and slice.
In crock-pot, combine beans, tomatoes, peppers and liquid.
Add ground beef mixture.
Add up to 2 cups of water. Cook on high until bubbling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours or cook on low overnight.

title: sour cream chili bake
directions: Brown beef.
Drain.
Stir in pinto beans, enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, 1 cup cheese and onion.
Set aside 1 cup chips and crush the rest.
Stir in meat mixture.
Turn into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Spoon sour cream atop.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Sprinkle chips around edge.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into large marble size balls. Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: can't fail pie crust
directions: Place flour in bowl; add salt and mix well.
Cut in shortening; add milk.
Stir until mixture clings together.
Put on floured board and knead lightly.
Roll thin.
Put in pie plate and prick with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal banana cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add egg, beat well. Add banana, oats, nuts and dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes.

title: chocolate sundae float
directions: Blend all in blender at high speed until smooth (or, mash banana then beat all with eggbeater or shake well in covered jar).
Serve with cinnamon stick for a stirrer if desired.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar, blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal spread on greased 13x9 pan. Bake 350° 20-25 minutes.

title: surprise pie or "impossible"
directions: Place eggs, margarine, sugar, flour and milk in a blender at high speed for 1 minute.
Whether using chocolate chips or coconut, add and blend only a few seconds.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie plate. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Pie forms its own crust.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well.
Stand out of fridge all day; return to fridge at night.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Put salt and pepper on meat.
Place in deep ovenproof dish. Add spices and vegetables.
Heat vinegar and water to boiling. Pour over meat.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Let marinate 48 hours, turning meat twice a day.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Mix well.
Stuff, roll and arrange in pan for cooking.
Ends of grape leaves are always folded in to secure filling.
Fill pot with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 40 minutes or until done. Add water if necessary.
Pour any excess water out and serve.

title: hot polish potato salad(enough for a food day group)
directions: *Mary says that "to crozzle" is to fry and crumble, so it can be sprinkled.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cider. Tie spices in small cheesecloth bag; add to cider mixture. Slowly bring to boil; simmer, covered, about 20 minutes. Use cinnamon sticks as muddlers. Makes 10 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt in a large pan.
Put ice on them and let them stand for 4 hours.
Drain well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding, milk, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix; repeat once.
Cover with either another 8 ounces of Cool Whip or meringue.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and gumdrops into small pieces.
Dredge with flour. Add coconut, condensed milk and pecans; mix well.
Pour into greased wax paper lined loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly.

title: chicken, bean and rice casserole
directions: Combine the rice and parsley in an 8 x 12-inch nonstick baking dish.
Make a white sauce of the broth, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Combine the chicken, beans, mushrooms and sauce.
Place the mixture over the rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle chopped onion and cheese over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6 with 220 calories.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well; put into flour/paprika mixture and pan-fry.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix together in a separate bowl the flour, salt and baking powder. Chill dough.
Roll dough to about 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into squares (or favorite cookie cutter).
Prick with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet covered with foil at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 60 minutes.

title: eggs ranchero
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice onion and green pepper. Cook in oil until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder and oregano (jalapenos, if you dare).
Cook slowly until sauce thickens slightly, about 20 minutes.
Pour into shallow baking dish. Drop eggs in, one at a time, carefully. Scatter cheese and olives on top and bake until firm.

title: pasta with tomato and bacon sauce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
Pour all grease except 1 tablespoon from skillet.
Add olive oil and onions to skillet. Saute onions until wilted.
Stir in garlic, tomatoes, salt, sugar and red pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes to reduce liquid.
Crumble bacon and add along with parsley.
Serve over pasta and garnish with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cookie owls(makes 2 dozen cookies)
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter; blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture and blend well. Stir in oats.
Divide dough in half.
Shape one half to form a roll 8 inches long.
Add chocolate to other half.
Roll out chocolate dough on waxed paper to form an 8-inch square.
Place roll on chocolate dough; wrap chocolate dough around roll.
Pinch seam together.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill for at least an hour. Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13 inch pan, add onion and Veg-all.
Mix the chicken broth and cream of chicken soup together and pour over the chicken and Veg-all.
Mix flour, salt and buttermilk together and pour over the chicken.
Pour melted butter over top of dough and bake in 425 oven for 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients. Mix and drop on cookie sheet. Let cookies harden and serve.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in
salt
and
water.
Add cheese, margarine and eggs in milk.
Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit rolls
directions: Blend the flour and margarine until crumbly.
Add egg yolk and sour cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cover with cheese slices until melted.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Then brown beef, onions, and peppers.
Stir in flour, then tomatoes.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook the macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
When sauce thickens, stir in cheese, macaroni, and seasonings.
Mix well.
Turn mixture into large buttered casserole and bake at 375 degrees, uncovered until bubbly and browned on top, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southern-style honey barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken skin side down in single layer in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine onion, tomato sauce, honey, vinegar, Worcestershire, paprika and pepper sauce.
Mix well; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes longer or until chicken is glazed and thoroughly cooked.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple and pudding together and chill 10 minutes.
Add the marshmallows, Cool Whip, nuts and coconut. Top with cherries and oranges.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Place milk in 4-cup bowl.
Heat in microwave on Level 8 (Medium High) 5 to 6 minutes until scalded.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in 2-quart bowl.
Stir hot milk in slowly.
Stir about 3/4 cup hot milk in yolks.
Stir constantly.
Return egg mix to bowl.
Cook Level 8 for 5 to 6 minutes until thick.
Stir often. Add coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash the shrimp into pulp and mix with remaining ingredients.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Spread dough on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let crust cool.
Combine cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spread onto cooled crust. Place finely chopped vegetables on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
(Vegetables may vary according to taste.)

title: davey crocketts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° on greased and floured cookie sheet, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: super-crisp veggie chips
directions: Use any root vegetables.
Scrub and thoroughly dry all vegetables.
Next, use a vegetable peeler or slicer to make extra-thin slices; this will ensure that the chips bake evenly and have uniform crispness.
(When slicing beets, always wear an apron and rubber gloves.
Beet juice can stain clothing and skin.)

title: kelly cheese squares
directions: Let butter and cheese come to room temperature.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Stack 3 slices of bread and cut off crusts.
Spread cheese mixture on one slice.
Top with second slice and spread it with cheese.
Put third slice on top; cut the stacks in quarters.
Spread mixture on top and slides, but not on bottom.
Continue until mixture is used up.
Makes about 36 squares.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over pea mixture.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear up cake and place 1/2 of it in the bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of the Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk combination over cake. Then layer on strawberries.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate; slice and serve.
"Fruit of your choice may be used."

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together. Pour dressing over vegetables and let stand in refrigerator for several hours.

title: bailey's liquor
directions: Place all ingredients in the blender.
Mix for 2 minutes. Chill and serve.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all together and put into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Put kielbasa in pan with enough water to cover the meat.
Put cover on pot.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Eat hot or let cool.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In kettle of boiling water, cook broccoli 2 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon into colander. Rinse with cold water until cool; place in bowl. Cook carrots and then green beans in some water 1 1/2 minutes. Remove, cool and add to broccoli.
In some water, cook pasta as label directs.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in a saucepan with chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in
shredded carrots.
Fold in cooked squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or crackers and butter; spread half of stuffing mix in the bottom of a 12 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top of the stuffing mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand for 1 hour.
Add to mixture the remaining ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned soft molasses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Melt shortening in saucepan large enough for mixing cookies.
Stir in molasses and sugar.
Cool.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Beat about 20 strokes.
Shape into balls (golf ball size).
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes or until cookies have lightly browned.
Store in covered stone jar.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and dry pudding.
Add chopped nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: toffee bars
directions: Separate crackers and place in single layer on cookie sheet. Fill the entire sheet.
Melt butter and oleo or margarine in pan, add sugar and bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over crackers and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; combine rest of ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: brown sugar nut cookies
directions: Beat the butter or margarine and brown sugar until soft and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in nuts.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets to make 1-inch mounds.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients.
Gradually add salad oil. Stir until well blended.
Add celery and green onions.
Makes 1 cup, enough for 2 1/2 pounds cooked, chilled shrimp.
Serve over shredded lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onion, pepper and garlic. Saute until tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Serve over rice. Great with cornbread!

title: banana pudding 3
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then add condensed milk and mix.
Add cool whip, leaving small amount to spread on top when finished. Put small amount of pudding on bottom to stand up wafers around side and on bottom.
Layer wafers, pudding, bananas, ending with pudding on top.
Put Cool Whip on top and crunch up some wafers on top of that for decoration.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding like directions on box, then add cool whip to pudding.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of pan, then layer of sliced bananas.
Put pudding mixture on top.
Then layer of wafers, layer of sliced bananas.
Top with cool whip. Now, its ready to eat.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper.
Add onion, bell pepper and ground beef to pan, brown until ground beef is cooked thoroughly.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: ho-bo's dream corn bread
directions: Mix like any other corn bread.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased and floured iron frypan until brown.

title: no bake chocolate-peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first six ingredients and boil one minute.
Remove from stove and add oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper and let harden.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together well and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw hamburger on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drain beans and put on top of hamburger.
Cover with soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender, not brown.
In saucepan, beat eggs with fork, add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir over medium heat until hot, do not boil.
Place cooked onions in pie plate with crust, pour egg mixture over onion and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cut in wedges.
Great served with steak.

title: blackberry layer cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift cinnamon, cloves and flour.
Add soda to blackberries.
Add to mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.
Frost with favorite icing.

title: marguerite langford's marshmallow potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and mash.
Add sugar and butter (vanilla, if desired).
Place in greased baking dish and bake until light brown.
Place marshmallows on top and let melt and brown.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in the 2 cups boiling water; pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple, cream, cottage cheese and salt.
Best to chill overnight.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Mix together.
Add 6 chicken breasts.
Marinate 2 hours. Grill.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with mixer for about 3 minutes. Pour on bottom of plate.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and any other vegetable you may desire.
Top with grated cheese.

title: homemade lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Cook noodles 12 to 13 minutes. Drain and rinse in cold water. Butter pan.
Mix sauce in hamburger.
Mix cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese together. Put a layer of noodles, layer of ground beef and layer of cheese. Repeat as much as desired.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store 24 hours.
Will keep 1 year in refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Cook tomatoes for 15 minutes.
Add sugar, pepper, oregano and red pepper.
Stir well.
Fry onions and bell peppers in oil.
Pour into sauce.
Stir well.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir well. Simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and 1 cup of water for 5 minutes, leaving 1/2 cup liquid left.
Let cool.
Add soda.
Blend shortening with salt, spices and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and cooled raisins mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well. Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased and floured baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen soft puffy cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush
crackers and chip chestnuts.
Cook chicken until tender and
chip
into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, soups, water chestnuts and sour cream.
Line bottom of bowl with 1/2 of crackers;
pour soup and chicken over crackers.
Put other 1/2
of crackers
over the top. Slice butter over the top and bake 350° until hot
and
bubbly
(about
30 minutes).
Can be made ahead of time, warmed over, or frozen.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Layer first 11 ingredients in order in slow cooker.
Add water; do not stir.
Cover and cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or on low for 8 to 9 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in stewed tomatoes with juice and ham.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: old time stack cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar a little at a time and blend well. Add molasses and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. To this, add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Pour into well greased small pie pans or four 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes, if using pie pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes if using cake pans.
Split layers (if using cake pans) and put 1 teaspoon cloves and 2/3 cup sugar with applesauce.
Spread between layers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in heavy, medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic and onion and saute until tender, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool.

title: broccoli slaw salad
directions: Mix above ingredients in bowl - except for 2 pkgs. of noodles.
Separate noodles & sauce packages.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin tin; fill only 1/4 full.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken asparagus over rice
directions: Sprinkle Accent over chicken.
Saute chicken in vegetable oil until white.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Place asparagus on bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread chicken over asparagus. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pepper and curry.
Spread on chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
(I like to make 1 1/2 times the sauce.)

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add milk, then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix dry ingredients together and sift.
Gradually stir dry ingredients into mixture. Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: five layer bars
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, salt and butter.
Press mixture evenly over bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut over crumb crust, then scatter the chocolate chips over. Pour the condensed milk evenly over the chocolate.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool overnight and cut into bars.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Spread 1 can of rolls in bottom of a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream first two ingredients and then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix in a little bowl.

title: yankee doodle dandies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in chow mein noodles and chopped nuts until they are evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 36.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix in a large pan all fruits and nuts.
Melt marshmallows and butter.
Pour over fruit and nuts.
Add vanilla wafers.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack in loaf pans.
I line small loaf pans with Saran Wrap and pack in the cake mixture.
Does not have to be refrigerated but I prefer it.
Can be frozen in freezer for long time, wrapped very good.
Makes great gifts.
Cut in thin or thick slices to serve.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix all three together (by hand).
Spread in jelly roll pan. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 4 hours or freeze and take on picnic.

title: sunday dinner rolls
directions: Take these rolls out of freezer before Sunday school. They are ready to bake when you get home from church.

title: cheese and green pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place bread shell on baking sheet.
Spread cream cheese over shell to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until heated through. Meanwhile chop tomato; set aside.
In large bowl, combine vinegar, oil, salt, herb seasoning and pepper.
Crush garlic; add to dressing, and beat until blended.
Add salad greens and tomato and toss.
Remove pizza from oven and top with salad.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados; blend in lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour.
Pour into a greased dish. Sprinkle cheese on top, then crumbled Ritz crackers to cover. Pour on margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat this together with the mixer with oil and sugar.
Add chopped apples (fresh and juicy, not too fine).
Mix together with pecans, flour, soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 or 40 minutes. May take an hour or more.
Bake in oblong pan.

title: date pudding
directions: Dissolve brown sugar and warm water in baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over sugar and water mixture in dish.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 10 o 12.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Melt chips slowly in saucepan. Add cream cheese. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat, then add Cool Whip. Stir until well blended. Spoon into crust. Chill in fridge.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add
meat. Marinate 2 to 3 hours, turning once.
Especially tasty on steaks!

title: oyster cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over oysters just before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, the sugar, 1/4 cup butter, salt and yeast in a large bowl. Add warm water, warm milk and egg. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl frequently. Beat 1 minute on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently. Stir in the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle. Place dough on lightly floured surface. Knead about 5 minutes or until dough is smooth and springy. Place dough in a large bowl greased with shortening, turning dough to grease with shortening on all sides. Cover bowl loosely with plastic wrap

and let rise in warm place for 1 hour or double. Dough is ready if indentation remains when touched. Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with shortening. Gently push fish into dough to deflate. Divide dough in 15 equal pieces. Shape each piece into a ball. Place in pan. Brush with butter. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until double.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine cider, sugar, cracked cinnamon sticks, cloves and allspice in large saucepan.
Heat over very low heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Let stand several hours to let flavor develop.
Strain cider.
Return to saucepan.
Heat just until hot.
Serve garnished with cinnamon sticks.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Sprinkle jello over and mix well.
Chill.

title: sea fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a full boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chips, oleo and
vanilla. Beat and pour into a large buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 X 12 in. baking dish.
Bring chicken broth and soup to boil; remove from heat.
Pour broth mix over chicken. Mix margarine, flour, and buttermilk; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brown at 450° for 5-10 minutes.

title: turkey in the straw
directions: Thoroughly combine butter and salad dressing mix with spatula. Spread over turkey or chicken parts.
Roll in stuffing crumbs to coat; sprinkle with paprika.
Place pieces skin side up (not touching) in greased jelly roll pan or any shallow pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour, uncovered, and bake 45 minutes more or until fork-tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Enjoy!

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat
egg
whites until fluffy.
Stir in other ingredients. Drop
by
rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased wrapping paper on cookie sheet.
Bake until set and delicately browned. They spread during baking so when they come from the oven
shape into
mounds
by gathering in edges with fingers. Bake at
325° for
to
minutes.
Yield:
1/2 dozen macaroons.

title: fat charlie's pineapple cake
directions: Prepare 13 x 9-inch pan. Grease and flour.
Bake cake mix 18 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Place in refrigerator for 5 minutes. Beat cream cheese into pudding until well mixed. Spread on cool cake. Spread well drained pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Layer chopped nuts over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Mix all together in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave on medium high for 10 minutes. Serves 4.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Grease and flour muffin pan.
Beat eggs until thick and fluffy.
Gradually add oil.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, allspice, cinnamon, sugar, nuts and raisins.
Add zucchini mixture.
Pour into muffin pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant. Cut into cubes and cook in small amount of water for 15 minutes. Drain. Saute onion, parsley and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of the butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggplant, beef and rice. Season with salt and pepper.
Put in 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with 1/2 cup toasted bread cubes. Dot with remaining butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven or casserole, put meat.
Sprinkle flour; add vegetables, soup and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: butternuts
directions: Heat peanut butter and butter bits.
Add cereal.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in juices from pineapple and oranges.
Fold this mixture into the Cool Whip.
Add fruits, nuts and marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature, or soften in microwave. Process dried beef until finely chopped.
Mix all ingredients except 1/3 cup of processed beef.
Shape into ball and roll in the reserved beef.
Best when made a day early.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough as thin as possible, having no holes.
Mix remaining ingredients except meat and cheese.
Spread on dough. Layer pepperoni and cheese.
Roll like jelly roll.
Spread outside of roll with egg whites.
Bake 35 minute at 350°.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pie crust. Chill 1 hour.

title: heavenly lemon sherbet
directions: Using a vegetable peeler, carefully remove rind from lemon. Note:

When removing the yellow rind, be careful not to remove any of the white pith underneath or your sherbet will taste bitter. Position knife blade in a food processor bowl and add rind and sugar; process until rind is minced.
Spoon sugar mixture into a bowl.
Add milk and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: *You may use French vanilla, lemon, or chocolate pudding mix instead of pistachio, if you desire.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Layer squash, tomatoes and onion in medium size saucepan. Salt to taste.
Add margarine and very small amount of water since it makes it's own liquid.
Place lid on and turn heat to high, then when steam escapes, turn heat down to low or simmer and cook only until tender (about 10 minutes).
Turn heat off and add cheese.
Let set for a few minutes to melt the cheese.

title: steamed persimmon pudding
directions: In a bowl, mix together persimmon, sugar, egg and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Pour in melted butter and the chopped nuts.
Combine well and put in covered pudding mold. Steam in large pot filled with water halfway up the sides of the mold sitting on a rack.
Steam for 2 hours.
Remove from pot; uncover and cool.
Unmold onto serving dish.
Serve with Hard Sauce flavored with Grand Marnier or cognac and maybe some persimmon pulp given a whirl in the blender.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until onions are limp. Add flour, salt, pepper, garlic and sugar.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is golden brown. Add parsley, thyme, chicken stock and white wine. Simmer 45 minutes; add cognac.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash hot potatoes by hand.
When no lumps are left, add cream cheese in small pieces, then add butter. Beat well until cheese and butter are melted and completely mixed.
Mix in sour cream.
To milk, add eggs and onions.
Fold into potato mixture along with salt and pepper.
Beat well until light and fluffy.
Place in a 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: middle east peasant vegetable dish
directions: In a casserole dish, alternate layers of vegetables and cheeses.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine together and top vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french meat pie
directions: Place all ingredients, but mashed potatoes, in large saucepan with cover.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 6 to 8 hours, until all onion is dissolved and water is gone.
Add mashed potatoes and mix well.
Now you are ready to put in your favorite pie crust. Top with pie crust.
Bake in oven at 400° until crust is brown. This may be eaten cold or hot with beef or chicken gravy.
This mixture is great when used to stuff your turkey or chicken with.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and mix vegetables.
Mix Ranch dressing according to package directions.
Combine all.
Chill and serve.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Grease bottom of cookie sheet; heat oven to 350°.
Flatten biscuits out on pan, spread pizza sauce over, then layer toppings as desired. Bake until golden brown.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops using the oil.
Remove chops and place in large baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chops once halfway through cooking period.
Cover may be removed the last half of the cooking period.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meatballs with hyssop
directions: Mix all ingredients except sesame seed; form into soft, small meatballs.
Roll the balls in sesame seed until evenly coated, then fry quickly in hot oil.
Brown on all sides, then drain and serve warm as appetizers on cocktail sticks.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart casserole dish.
Peel carrots.
Slice diagonally.
Cook in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Prepare Basic Sour Cream Sauce.
Fold in carrots, parsley, onion and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Prepare bread crumbs to sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli.
Simmer broccoli, chicken broth and onions in a saucepan or slow-cook until tender.
Puree in food processor or blender.
Serve with lemon slices and parsley.
Makes 4 (1-cup) servings.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and put aside.
Place frozen hash browns in a very large bowl.
Add sour cream, cream of chicken soup, onion and cheeses; mix thoroughly.
Add margarine, salt and pepper; mix again.
Place everything into a 10 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place corn flake crumbs on top.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Take foil off and bake another 20 minutes.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: coconut jewel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in cherries and oats.
Shape dough to form 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks, pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat and add cottage cheese.
Chill until partially set.
Gradually beat 1/2 cup sugar into stiffly beaten egg whites. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into corn flake crust.

title: microwave jalapeno cheese ball
directions: In microwavable small bowl, microwave butter on High until melted.
Stir in onions; cook 30 seconds, or until wilted. Remove.
In large bowl, microwave cream cheese on Medium for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until soft.
Remove from oven.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until smooth.
On low speed, beat in green onions, jalapeno peppers to taste and Worcestershire sauce.
Transfer to a piece of plastic wrap; shape into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Roll in crushed chips.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Rub brisket with the salts and pepper.
Put in heavy-duty foil and pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Wrap with foil and marinate for 12 to 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cook in foil for 5 hours at 250°.
Take out of oven; pour juices in pan for gravy.
Pour Woody's cookin sauce over it.
Wrap tightly in foil and cook 1 more hour.
Pour juices off in pot; thicken to gravy and add small amount of catsup and Worcestershire, if desired.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cut meat in cubes.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Add flour and stir with fork to cover each piece.
Shake each piece off to remove excess flour.
Put each piece in shortening and let it cook for 15 or 20 minutes or until brown on medium heat.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour to brown for gravy.
Add 1/2 cup of water, then the other seasons and let it simmer for 10 minutes in the covered pot.
Serve over rice.
A serving for 4 or more.

title: cracker sandwich
directions: Cut meat into 4 pieces.
Cut cheese into 4 pieces.
Put meat on 1 cracker; put cheese on meat.
Smooth mustard on cheese on cracker.
Makes 2 cracker sandwiches.

title: caramel oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or less if you like chewy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix together corn flakes and butter; sprinkle over the top of the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or longer.
Serves 12.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Take a medium to large croissant and cut it in half.
Lay each half on a plate with cut side up.
Spread cream cheese over each half.
Take fruit and lay on top of cream cheese.
Enjoy!

title: grandma kellers dill pickles
directions: Put water, salt and vinegar together. Put on pickles, boiling hot and seal in jars.
Set in boiling water for 5 minutes or until they turn yellowish.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix all ingredients, adding corn bread last.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in frying pan.
Remove and drain.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or place all ingredients in slow cooker and set on low for about 2 to 3 hours.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: In a mixing bowl or punch bowl, blend together the sherbet, frozen lime concentrate and sugar.
Just before serving, stir in the soda and the crushed ice.
Pour and enjoy.
Makes 7 cups.

title: baked stuffed chicken(feeds 3 people.)
directions: Soak chicken gravy in stuffing until moist and soft, about 1/2 hour.
In 9-inch greased pie plate, spoon stuffing all around. Arrange chicken over stuffing; press lightly.
Combine sugar, margarine and mustard; spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.

title: quick chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat the first six ingredients 4 minutes at medium speed.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Enjoy!

title: brownies
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until light.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When partly cooled, cut into squares.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Over low heat or microwave, melt chips with margarine.
Mix in pudding,
extract and milk.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Shape in 1-inch balls; roll in finely ground nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: aunt lizzie's famous stew
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and onion (which have been chopped), bay leaves and seasoning.
Simmer for 2 hours; stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Forty-five minutes before done, add sliced carrots and quartered potatoes.
Top with dumplings 15 minutes before meal time.
Serves 8.

title: cherry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Add cherries, cream cheese and banana.
Refrigerate until cold.
Beat with 1 package prepared Dream Whip.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Put into casserole dish and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake until bubbly in a 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: grandma herr's cherry pudding cake
directions: Note:
Two cups well drained
canned
sour cherries can be used. In that case, use 1/2 cup juice and
1/2 cup milk instead of 1 cup milk for the liquid.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 5 minutes.
Add 3/4 roll garlic cheese and 3/4 stick oleo to grits mixture.
Beat eggs in 1-cup measure; add enough milk to beaten eggs to make 1 cup.
Add to grits mixture.
Put in greased casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place on top of grits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cheese lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine tomato and spaghetti sauces; set aside.
In another bowl, combine all cheeses; set aside.
In a buttered 12 x 8-inch baking pan, place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles and cover with 1/3 sauces and then cheeses.
Repeat layering 2 more times with noodles, sauces and cheeses.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Superfine sugar can be made by blending granulated sugar in a food processor for a few seconds.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine in skillet.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs or French fried onion rings.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the 1/3 cup sugar with the cornstarch and salt.
Blend in milk and then egg yolks.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into egg yolk mixture.
In pastry shell, alternate layers of banana slices and cream filling.
Cover and chill.
Top with whipped cream and additional sliced bananas to serve.

title: holiday cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine; top evenly with marshmallows, coconut and cherries.
Pour condensed milk evenly over cherries.
Top with nuts; press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool. Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator. Makes about 48 bars.

title: ham cheese cubes
directions: Beat all ingredients together (except ham) until creamy and of spreading consistency.
Place one ham slice on a piece of waxed paper.
With spatula, spread on some of creamed mixture.
Place another slice of ham on top; spread with more cheese.
Repeat, using 6 slices, ending with ham slice on top.
With slice number 7, start process again.
Wrap securely in waxed paper; place in freezer 2 hours or more.
About 1 hour before serving, remove from refrigerator and cut lengthwise and crosswise into 1/2-inch cubes. Pierce each cube with a toothpick.
Yield:
75 to 80 cubes.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain macaroni.
Add tuna, peas and onion; blend in mayonnaise.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix ingredients to a medium container of Mrs. Stratton's pimento cheese spread.
Mix well and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: honey muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients in then bake in muffin pans which are greased and coated with flour.

title: buttercream vanilla frosting
directions: Combine butter, salt, vanilla and 1 cup of sugar.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately; mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed for good spreading consistency.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar, butter, vanilla and cinnamon in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in milk.
Pour cream cheese mixture over bread in large bowl; toss lightly.
Let stand 15 minutes, rearranging bread in bowl occasionally to moisten evenly.
Arrange bread in rows in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining cream cheese mixture over bread.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Saute hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Add spices and sugar.
Simmer several hours.
Pour over spaghetti to serve.

title: apple pie
directions: Divide in two parts.
Put small slits in the top crust; brown until done at 425°, about 40 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in strips (trim of fat or gristle).
Season with flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper, then fry in large skillet in small amount of oil.
Add 1 3/4 cups water, juice from tomatoes, chopped onion and gravy base.
Let simmer about 1 hour or until tender.
Add canned tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce. Cook 5 minutes and serve over rice.

title: traditional biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Measure flour into medium bowl.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir milk in until dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into a ball.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese (room temperature) with 1/2 cup milk until fairly smooth.
Add pudding mix and remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spread on top of cake.
Spread the pineapple over the pudding layer.
Spread the whipped topping over pineapple and, if desired, sprinkle with the nuts.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours before serving.

title: puppy chow(chex muddy buddies)
directions: In 1-quart microwavable bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth; stir after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour cereals into large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into a large resealable bag with powdered sugar.
Seal bag securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: crab mold dip
directions: Heat soup and gelatine.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add all to soup mixture and place in mold. Refrigerate.
Use as an appetizer served with your favorite crackers.

title: betty's creamed spinach
directions: Boil spinach as directed. Salt to taste. Drain and set aside. Saut onion and garlic in butter. Add spinach and cream cheese. Add Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle garlic powder, onion powder and pepper to taste.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sprite.
Put in gallon milk jug and fill the rest with water.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, add bottle of Sprite.

title: meatballs 'n mashed potatoes
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, egg and seasonings.
Form into 1-inch balls. Brown in skillet.
Add 2 cans tomato soup.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Season to taste.
Use sauce from meatballs to spoon over potatoes as gravy.
Serves 4.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in
blender to be the consistency of soft cream cheese.
Pour into bowl; add jello.
Mix.
Add Cool Whip, folding in gently.	Lastly,
fold
in the cherries.
Set in refrigerator to set.

title: fill'er up oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix wet ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cook on hot griddle about 4 to 5 minutes on each side for each cake.
Feeds six hungry people.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Put into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan in the order given.
Do not mix!
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix onion soup, Catalina dressing and cranberry sauce.
Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Cover with soup, dressing and cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: fried apples
directions: Peel 5 pounds green apples (Granny Smith).
Put 3/4 stick butter in pan and let melt on low.
Cut up apples, discard cores and place in pan.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water, cover and cook on medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
When apples are tender, remove top and let liquid evaporate.
This is great for breakfast with Virginia ham and eggs.
Also good cold with vanilla ice cream.

title: martha patch's company strawberry soup
directions: Stir sugar into sour cream.
Stir in Burgundy and whipped cream.
Fold in berries.
Chill.
May be served as appetizer, dessert or begin a Summer meal with a strawberry soup.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate drink mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 3 or 4 heaping teaspoonfuls for 1 cup water (hot or cold).

title: squash preserves
directions: Peel and cut up squash after removing seed.
Cover with sugar (enough to cover well).
Put in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning cook on low heat real slow; add 1/2 cup lemon juice and 1/2 cup Karo syrup.
Cook until squash is tender and juice is thick.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: apple delicious pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and apple chunks in prepared pastry crust. Put on top crust. Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top crust. Bake at 450° for 1 hour in a paper bag. (Gas oven only.)

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Pierce brisket all over with a fork.
Sprinkle brisket with liquid smoke and tenderizing salt.
Put brisket on rack in roasting pan.
Combine onion salt, nutmeg, pepper, garlic salt and paprika in a cup; mix well.
Sprinkle over brisket.
Coat entire top of meat with brown sugar.
Cover with foil; roast in a slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes per pound.
Remove meat to warm platter; let stand 20 minutes.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in plastic container and freeze.
Serve with equal parts mix and 7-Up.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it starts to boil.
Pour into prepared pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Refrigerate until set.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in slow cooker; simmer until ready to eat. Serve with chips.

title: veal loaf
directions: Form loaf and bake 1 hour.
Put cracker crumbs on top and baste with milk and water.

title: norwegian brownies
directions: Put
all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer on medium
speed
until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed. Pour into brownie pan or rectangular biscuit pan and bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Put vinegar and butter in a double boiler until butter is melted.
Add all other ingredients, mixed together well.
Cook until thick.

title: kings coffee
directions: Combine coffee and water.
Add cinnamon.
Chill.
Pour cinnamon-flavored coffee into 6 chilled glasses filled with crushed ice.
Add 1 ounce brandy to each glass.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken with nuts
directions: Stir-fry walnuts in small amount of olive oil a few minutes. Remove from pan.
Be sure to take nuts out before they darken or they will taste bitter.
Stir-fry chicken until they are no longer pink.
Push chicken to one side of pan.
Stir-fry celery until they are bright green.
Return nuts back to pan and add chicken broth and stir in cornstarch paste (2 teaspoons cornstarch and enough water to form paste) to thicken.
Serve immediately with brown rice.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix together thoroughly and put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Take from oven and stir.
Save 3/4 cup for topping.
Press remaining crumbs into pan and set aside.

title: carley's chocolate buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl and set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips and peanut butter. Microwave 1 1/2 to 5 minutes (depending on your microwave) until smooth.
Pour wet mixture over Chex.
Mix with a large spoon to make sure all Chex are coated.
Pour chocolate Chex in a large resealable bag with powdered sugar.
Mix.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots (thick slices). Cook just until tender and drain. Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved. Pour over carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and chill in refrigerator. Can be served hot or cold.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti.
Add the McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning and the Robusto dressing.
Toss with the cut up cucumber, tomato, green pepper and celery.
Best made the night before.

title: mixed vegetable bake
directions: In large sauce pan, cook carrots and green beans in boiling water until crisp tender (or steam them).
Drain.
Place in 2 quart casserole.	In medium sauce pan, melt butter; add onion, herbs and mushrooms.	Saute until tender.
Spoon mixture over carrots and beans; top with tomato wedges and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
12 (1/2 c.) servings.

title: victoria sandwich(heritage:  english)
directions: Grease and line base of two 7-inch round cake pans lined with waxed paper.
Cream the butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in lightly whisked eggs a little at a time, beating after each addition to prevent curdling.

Use a metal spoon to carefully and evenly fold in sifted flour and salt. If required, add a little warm water to make a soft dropping consistency. Divide mixture between the prepared tins and spread evenly.
Bake just above the center in a 375° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes until well risen and golden brown. Leave in tins for a minute, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool.
When cold, sandwich together with jelly.
Sprinkle sugar very lightly over the top.

title: beefy mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine cornmeal, eggs, milk, corn, oil and salt in bowl; mix well.
Pour half the corn bread batter into greased large cast-iron skillet sprinkled with additional cornmeal.
Layer ground beef, onion and cheese in prepared skillet.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Yield:
4 servings.

title: mr. ross's chili
directions: Cook meat and onion in open skillet until done.
Drain off excess fat. Put meat, chili seasoning, beans, water and tomato juice in an open kettle and bring to a boil.
Stir in cornmeal a little at a time.
Salt to taste and cook over low fire for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in bowl.
Make one layer of mixture.
Put cheese on top of this.
Put remaining mixture on top of cheese.
Add a little ketchup on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
This makes 6 servings.

title: egg and olive mix
directions: Chop eggs with pastry blender.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Use for dip or sandwich spread.
Best when made the day before.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat while macaroni is cooking.
Grate cheese.
Using an ovenproof bowl, spray with Pam.
Put 1 cup macaroni in the bottom. Cover it with cheese, then with the meat.
Cover with cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Pour milk all over the top. Make sure there's an edge all around the bowl.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate. Remove 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: peach frozen yogurt
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a saucepan; let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat and add sugar and salt, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stir in yogurt, vanilla and finely chopped peaches. Cover and chill.
Unused portion should be placed in freezer. About 82 calories per 1/2-cup serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and put into a casserole dish.
Crust Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top mixed with some grated cheese. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours (or high 4 to 5 hours). Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
May be doubled.

title: amaretto pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies and melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie pan.
Chill well or bake at 300° for 12 minutes (watch carefully).
Cool.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: First, brown ground beef, then drain.
In same skillet, mix in corn and Ranch Style beans, then add chili powder to taste.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer bottom of pan with tortillas.
May have to tear in pieces to cover.
Next, layer half of ground beef mixture, then add layer of cheese to cover completely.
Next, add layer of tortillas, then ground beef mixture, then cheese, then 1 more layer of tortillas.
In small bowl, mix the Ro-Tel and the soup together.
Pour on top and bake in a 400° oven until bubbly.

title: firey cajun shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix together butter, margarine, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, rosemary, Tabasco sauce, salt, garlic and lemon juice.
Divide half the mixture between 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking dishes.
Arrange shrimp and lemon slices on top of sauce to about 1-inch from rim of dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shrimp and lemon; bake, uncovered, stirring once or twice until shrimp are cooked, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with hot French bread for dipping.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate marshmallow slices
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chocolate chips until blended.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows and 1 cup nuts.
Do not allow marshmallows to melt.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into a greased 8-inch baking pan.
Chill. Yield:
About 4 dozen.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix nuts, coconut and Jell-O.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well. Cover and chill at least one hour.
Shape mixture into strawberry shape and roll in red sugar.
Dip end in green sugar.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix ingredients together except tomatoes. When serving, top with the tomatoes. Let set overnight or at least several hours. (I chop all my ingredients very fine.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: First you get a chunk of leftover biscuit dough.
You mash it out round about this big?
Grease the baker sparingly.
Put the dough on the baker and shoot the fire to it, but not too much or it will be raw in the middle.
When it browns on one side, flip it over and brown on the other side.
Get the butter, I mean "cow butter" and the syrup pitcher full of homemade syrup.
"That's when the sopping begins."
This is especially good anytime you can get it.

title: bushwackers
directions: In a blender, combine listed ingredients.
Add enough ice to fill at least 1/2 of the blender; blend until slushy.
Drink at your own risk.

title: special five hour stew
directions: Spread stew meat over bottom of roaster or Dutch oven.
Cut vegetables into big chunks over meat.
Pour canned tomatoes and can of water over all.
Sprinkle with tapioca and seasonings. Cover and bake at 275° for 4 hours. Then remove cover.
Stir and bake 1 hour longer.
Serve with tossed salad and rolls.

title: tortilla black bean casserole
directions: Bring to a boil: onion, pepper, picante sauce, tomatoes and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Stir in beans.
Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole, spread 1/3 bean mixture.
Top with half of tortillas.
Top with half the cheese.
Repeat: bean, tortilla, bean, then the remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nut "sheet" cookies
directions: Need lots of cookies in a hurry?
These kick off with cake mix so make in minutes.
Combine cake mix with oil, banana, egg and cinnamon.
Add walnuts and prunes or raisins.
Spread level in two greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until tops start feeling firm when touched lightly.
Cool in pans or racks.
Cut bars or squares.

title: party ryes(appetizers)
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients. Spread on bread slices. Arrange on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: guess again carrots
directions: Put into 1 quart buttered casserole dish add a little butter on top Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Can use raw, unsalted whole almonds and chop them.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Combine first three ingredients in pan.
Stir over medium heat until all liquid evaporates.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove, stir and sprinkle with salt.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Stir and bake 10 more minutes.
Let cool. Store covered.
Yields approximately 6 cups.

title: garlic butter
directions: Combine the butter or margarine, parsley and Accent.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Add milk and melted butter to the egg.
Combine the 2 mixtures with a few turns of the spoon.
Fold in chopped apples.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased muffin tin.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon made from 4 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dad's clam chowder
directions: Drain the clams, reserving the liquid to add later.
Simmer the potatoes, onion and celery in medium pan covered with just enough water to cover, until done (about 20 minutes).
Do not use too much water as water and all goes in soup.
In large pot, melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add cream and let thicken by itself.
Add undrained veggies, clams and clam juice to milk mixture in large pan.
Heat 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg; add milk and melted butter.
Put corn, crumbs and cheese
in	layers into casserole.	Pour liquid over top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: simple roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven. Combine next ingredients and pour over roast.
Add onion.
Cover and simmer on top of stove or bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Add potatoes, cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; melt butter and saute onion.
Add meat; brown and remove.
Add flour, catsup, broth and dill to butter; add mushrooms and saute.
Add meat and warm sour cream. Serve over noodles.

title: easy poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Spray 2 loaf pans with cooking oil (Pam).
Pour mixture into loaf pans; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle crackers on top and drizzle margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: marinated salad
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into chunks.
Mix oil, wine vinegar, sugar, dry seasoning, mustard and salt.
Pour over vegetables and chill for at least 3 hours.

title: luau barbecue beans
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Add beans.
Heat; stir now and then.
Serve.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or margarine.
Saute celery and onion for 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes, water, pepper and bay leaf. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and cook occasionally. Remove bay leaf.
Gradually add soup and milk.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Boil broccoli 3 minutes, drain.
Beat eggs, melt butter, and mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 13x9 baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees until brown, 40-50 minutes.

title: coconut cherry bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Spread over first layer; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook cream of chicken soup with the milk.
When it starts to boil, add the Velveeta cheese.
Cook until it melts.
Take a baking dish and arrange cooked chicken on the bottom, then add broccoli on top.
Pour soup mixture on top of broccoli.
