Sprinkle 1/2 cup of Ritz crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until casserole starts bubbling.
Serve over white rice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add 2 cups of flour with baking powder.
Add all extract.
Use 2 cups of flour to dredge fruit and nuts.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Let stand overnight.

title: strawberry-walnut bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts in bottom of each pan.
Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cardamon, salt and nutmeg. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened. Stir in remaining nuts. Spoon batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Add sour cream and parmesan cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice according to directions; set aside.
Saute onion and celery in butter until soft and clear. Cook broccoli and drain.
In a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole, combine all ingredients and bake, uncovered, until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: granola bars
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and honey.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Stir in oats, Rice Krispies, chocolate chips and seeds.
Grind dried fruit to a sticky consistency and stir in.
Line an 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan with foil.
Spray with coating.
With damp fingers, spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, invert and peel off foil.
Store airtight.
Freezes well.
I often let the kids have these for breakfast.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts 30 minutes.
Discard bones and skin. Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with broccoli.
Top with chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, paprika and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix crumbs in butter and spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach or broccoli souffle
directions: Note:
If using spinach, one package drain and squeeze well. Repeat.

title: eva's noodle casserole
directions: In a skillet brown meat and celery.
Cook your noodles to al dente according to package directions.
Next butter your casserole dish. Layer into casserole as follows:
1/2 noodle, 1/2 meat, 1/2 can stewed tomatoes, 1/2 can soup.
Then repeat.
When done, cover with cheddar cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Cream margarine with sugar substitute.
Combine soda and applesauce and add to margarine mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; stir just until blended.
(Do not overmix.) Pour into nonstick 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cake is cool, cut into 15 equal slices.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix; sprinkle with a layer of coconut.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple-oatmeal bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and whole grain flour. Cream in a large bowl shortening, sugar, egg, grated apples and juice.
Add the sifted ingredients alternately to the fruit mixture with the buttermilk.
Stir in the batter with a few strokes the nuts and oatmeal.
Place the dough in a greased loaf pan.
Bake the bread 1 1/4 hours, letting it cool in the pan.

title: tea punch
directions: Boil water and place tea bags in water to soak.
When soaked, mix with all other ingredients together in gallon jug and finish filling with water.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and press into the bottom of an 8 x 8 inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine vinegar, salt, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Chop tomatoes.
Add to vinegar mixture.
Stir in peppers and olives.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Bake and cool 2 pie crusts. Slowly cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick. Cool pineapple mixture. Slice 1 banana in bottom of each pie crust. Pour 1/2 of cooled pineapple mixture on each crust. Top each pie with Cool Whip. Top with toasted coconut. Chill.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in dish.
Put all ingredients in and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to box directions.
Mix pineapple and Miracle Whip (more Miracle Whip may be added).
Mix together. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle top with oregano.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove core from whole head of cabbage with a sharp knife. Scald the cabbage in boiling water.
Remove a few leaves at a time.

title: veggies with lemon sauce
directions: In pot with steamer basket, boil 3-inches water.
Steam potatoes 10 minutes, then add peppers and broccoli for 5 minutes more or until tender.
Place in serving dish and keep warm.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, lemon juice and thyme.
Heat over low heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over vegetables and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in bacon and corn.
Add liquid ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 18 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 12 muffins.

title: homemade bread
directions: Heat milk and butter together until almost boiling; add sugar and salt and cool to warm to touch.
Add eggs and yeast, then flour to make soft dough.
Let rise about 1 hour; punch down and put into pans for rolls or bread.
Let rise again 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven until light brown.
Makes 8 loaves of bread.

title: mountain breeze fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts in large bowl; let stand 1 hour, stirring often.

title: chicken bog
directions: Boil chicken in about 4 cups water.
Add onion until tender. Add water if necessary.
Remove and debone chicken.
Add chicken pieces, sausage, pepper and rice to liquid; simmer until broth evaporates.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil jalapeno peppers and tomatoes.
Add half the garlic and black pepper.
Add salt.
Simmer until tender.
Put mixture in blender.
Add can of tomato paste and chopped green onions.
Add rest of garlic and black pepper.
Liquify in blender.
Let cool and store in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Chop boiled eggs and onion.
Mix these with soup, milk and crackers, then add chunks of cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Crush more crackers and spread on top. Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: baked crispy-topped apples
directions: Cut apples in half crosswise and core.
Put apples cut side up in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Blend syrup, margarine and cinnamon.
Add cereal; toss to coat.
Spoon over apples.
Bake uncovered at 350° until apples are fork-tender, about 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: herbed chicken in sauce
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in margarine. Arrange in a baking dish.

title: baked beans
directions: In 1-quart baking dish, combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meats and add uncooked rice, chopped celery, soup and water. Cook about 15 min. Add salt and pepper to taste and soy sauce.

title: nut roll and poppyseed roll
directions: Have milk lukewarm.
Mix yeast with 3 tablespoons warm water and add to milk.
To this, add sugar, salt, oil, then the egg yolks and egg whites.
Add the flour a little at a time.
Let rise in a warm place, covered, about 2 hours.
Then take 1 ball of dough at a time and roll out 1/2-inch thick on a floured board, being careful not to use a rolling pin very much, just stretch as much as possible with the hands.
Spread with nuts or other fillings such as poppyseed, prune or apricot filling.
Roll up like jelly roll and place on greased pan.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes. Brush with milk and bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh cherry pie
directions: Combine cherries, sugar, tapioca, lemon peel and salt.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Fill pie shell with cherry mixture.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix spaghetti sauce, browned hamburger and oregano together.
In greased 9 x 9-inch pan, make layers using half each of noodles, hamburger-sauce mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Add unbeaten egg and blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch pan 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: green chili pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain fat.
Add chopped onion and cook slightly.
Add salt and water and thicken with white corn meal.
Stir in green chilies.
Remove from heat.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 cup of Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1 cup of sauce, 3 noodles and half of cheese mixture. Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella.
Pour 3/4 cup water around the edges of the pan (less if you use more sauce).
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: huckleberry pie
directions: Put sugar, water and lemon juice on to boil.
When it starts to boil, remove from heat.
Add 1 cup of berries, mixed with cornstarch.
Let cool, then add remaining 3 cups berries.
Blend together and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: zee's quiche
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate with butter.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom of pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth, 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour over ingredients in pie plate and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce-spice bars(spanish bar loaf)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix all ingredients except frosting.
Spread in pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes. Cool; frost.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: In a small saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in pineapple juice and egg.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick; add lemon juice.
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion; cook until tender and drain.
Combine sour cream, carrots and soup and stir in squash and onion.
In another pan, melt butter and mix in with stuffing mix; pour in squash and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: fancy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms thoroughly.
Break off stems and chop them up. Saute onions in butter.
When onions are translucent, add sausage that has been pushed out of casing or peeled of casing.
Warm through.
Add bread crumbs and mushroom stems.
Continue to cook over medium-low heat for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine gelatin in boiling water.
Fold in all at once all the remaining ingredients except the sour cream.
Turn half of mixture into baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Then evenly spread top with sour cream.
Gently spoon on rest of mixture, refrigerate. Cut when firm and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cove with foil.
Bake at 350 for one hour, stirring at 30 minutes.

title: cheddar spinach spread
directions: Saute onions and spinach in bacon grease until tender.
Chop spinach.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
Heat 30 to 45 minutes (in a small casserole dish) in 350° oven.
Garnish with black olives and a spinach leaf.
Serve with Swiss cheese crackers.
Makes 2 cups spread.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Chop onions (ends and all).
Crush and mince garlic cloves. Mix onions, garlic, cheese and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut bread in half lengthways.
Spread topping on both halves.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: cherry cheese cakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each muffin cup.
Spoon 1 teaspoon mixture in each muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool. Top with cherry pie filling.
These freeze well.
Defrost and top with filling.
Can use blueberry pie filling. Yields 35 to 40 cheese cakes.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine or butter; set aside.
Crush the vanilla wafers in a baggie; save 3/4 cup.
Stir the melted butter well into the crumbs so that they all get moistened.
Press crumb mixture in the bottom of 11 x 13-inch Pyrex dish; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix sugar and soft (but not liquid) margarine.
Add 2 well-beaten eggs; mix well.
Pour over crumbs.
Slice strawberries.
Spread evenly over sugar mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip or Reddi-Wip.
Garnish with saved crumbs.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: In a
medium
bowl, combine first 7 ingredients and set aside. In
a
large mixing bowl, combine sugars, oil, buttermilk, vanilla
and
eggs;
stir until all ingredients are well blended. Add
flour
mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and walnuts, stirring
just until blended.
Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease
3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Cut rounds of wax paper to fit
pans
and line bottoms of pans with it.
Grease and flour wax paper.
Pour batter evenly into pans.
Bake for 30 minutes
or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool
in pans for 10 minutes; loosen cake layers from sides of
pans
with a
sharp knife.
Invert onto wire racks. Peel off
wax
paper
and let
cool completely.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting
between layers,
on
top
and sides of cake. Cover and refrigerate overnight before you cut.

title: noodles(no fail; no tough)
directions: Mix well.
Roll thin.
Let lay and dry for 15 to 20 minutes. Cut desired width.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, bananas and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix and chill overnight. Form into balls and dip into melted chocolate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Lightly pound the cutlets to make them into thin fillets.
Melt half the butter and saute the onion, parsley, and celery over gentle heat.
Add the seasonings.
Remove from the heat and place in a bowl.
Add the bread crumbs, dampened with a bit of water and mix gently.
Divide into 8 equal portions and place each on a pork fillet.
Roll and secure with a skewer or tie with string.
Dredge in flour sprinkled on waxed paper.
Brown in a frying pan, using the rest of the butter.
Add the chicken stock, lower the heat, cover and cook very slowly, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well. Shape into ball. Chill. Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add all ingredients, except the potato chips.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add crushed potato chips on top.
Bake approximately 10 more minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, milk and broth in large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Stir stuffing mix with chicken mixture, saving 1 cup to sprinkle on top.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with slices of cheese.
Cover with a layer of macaroni, salt and pepper.
Layer this way until full.
Add milk.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir contents at 15 minute mark.

title: refrigerator all-bran rolls
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
shortening, bran, sugar and salt. Stir
until
shortening
is dissolved.
In the lukewarm water crumble
the
2 cakes of yeast.
Beat eggs and add yeast mixture. Add
this to the first mixture.
Add flour until the dough is just beyond the sticky or glazed look.
Cover tightly and store
in refrigerator
until 3 hours before using.
Work out into
rolls and
let
rise where the temperature is 75 to 80°.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen rolls. If you
don't
need it
all at once, the remaining dough will keep in the refrigerator, tightly covered, for several days.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Cream butter with 2 1/2 cups sugar, then add egg yolks, one at a time.
Turn in sour cream and flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat whites until stiff and add 1/2 cup sugar to eggs, then fold into batter.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool on wet cloth after removing.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash in 1 1/2 cups water with 1/2 onion (drain if watery).
Stir in 1/2 onion, bell pepper, celery, eggs and everything else.
Add cornbread to make to the right consistency. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Mix the first three ingredients with electric mixer.
Put 1/2 of mixture into greased casserole.
Put layer of whole marshmallows.
Put on remainder of potato mixture.
Over this put brown sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat bananas with electric mixer.
Add shortening and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine baking soda with milk and then add to banana mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in sugar, salt, Crisco, eggs, potatoes and half of flour.
Mix in remaining flour until easy to handle.
Turn onto floured board and knead.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before baking.
Make into crescents.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bud's best apple crumb pie
directions: Peel apples; slice into pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Work together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 10 minutes, then for 45 minutes at 350° or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt butter in a bit pot on low heat; add milk.
Put in all 3 bags of morsels and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallows and pecans; stir until mixed good.
Pour into flat pan.
Put in refrigerator for about 2 hours (optional).
For a better taste, add more pecans on top.

title: tasty applesauce pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, turn the applesauce and brown sugar. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes; removed from heat.
Add 1/4 cup butter and the salt; stir until butter is melted.
Stir in raisins.
Cool to room temperature.
In a small mixing bowl, beat the eggs well; add to cooled applesauce mixture and blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven on rack below center, for 20 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Cut shortening, flour and salt until crumbly.
Beat remaining ingredients together and add to flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until just blended.
Don't overstir.
Refrigerate for an hour before rolling out.
Turn pastry out on well-floured surface. Makes three 9-inch pie crusts.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add soda and chill until thickened.
Add fruit and pour into serving bowl or individual dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped topping and fruit, if desired.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: mother's barbecue sauce
directions: Cut meat into cubes for pot barbecue.
Cook cubed meat in water in stock pot until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook down until desired texture is reached.

title: molded cherries jubilee(makes 6 servings)
directions: Drain syrup from cherries into pint measuring cup; add water to measure 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Bring to simmering in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add Port, almonds and drained cherries.
Spoon into dessert dishes and chill until firm.
Top with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream just before serving

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press evenly onto bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake until no indentation when touched, about 25 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 25.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch casserole in oven.
Mix remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese rolls
directions: Heat cottage cheese and water to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast in mixture.
Combine sugar, salt, soda, yeast, cottage cheese and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat with a mixer.
Then stir in rest of flour by hand. Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Let rise until doubled in a greased bowl.
Then punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise again until doubled and then bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 30 rolls.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned; drain well and set aside.
Pour half of cornbread mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with ground meat and top with cheese, onion and peppers. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: persian apricots
directions: Blend ground almonds and extract into almond filling.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of almond mixture into middle of each apricot.
Place on waxed paper to dry slightly.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Can be made two weeks ahead.
Makes 48 pieces.

title: bubble mix
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into large oblong aluminum roaster. Small plastic berry boxes work great to make small bubbles.
This mixture can be saved to use again.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Place 3 to 4 tablespoons of mixture on tortilla.
Sprinkle generously with cheese and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Spread remaining mixture on top of rolled tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
This dish freezes well.

title: preserve cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Set aside. Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time. Beat well. Stir in flour alternately with buttermilk.
Beat until smooth. Mix vanilla preserves and pecans together. Fold into batter until blended. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Mix into pancake type batter and pour into greased frying pan or griddle.
Keep each cake small enough to turn easily.
Cook as you would pancakes; butter and eat hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl, then make well in center and pour in oil.
Add pumpkin and cold water; blend well with beater.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour batter into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: walnut nut torte
directions: Grease and line 2 pans.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Beat yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick and light in color.
On low speed add bread crumbs and baking powder, then walnuts into yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in pans and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 5 minutes and then take out of pans.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops and place in roaster.
Mix bread cubes, margarine, seasoning, onion and 1/4 cup water well and spread over chops.
Mix soup and 1/3 cup water until smooth; pour over dressing and chops.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour (cover pan until the last 5 to 10 minutes).

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Add tomato, pepper, pimento, onion, pickles, cheese and ham or other meat; toss together.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir in macaroni mixture.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Slightly cook ground beef.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: christmas cream cheese turnovers
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter in bowl.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out thin on floured surface.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Place 2 cherries from cherry pie filling in center of each square.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen turnovers.

title: sensational spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together sausage, Ricotta cheese, spinach, cream cheese, Mozzarella cheese, 2 eggs and hot pepper sauce in large bowl until well blended.
On lightly floured surface, roll out one pie crust to 12-inch circle.
Place in 10-inch pie plate.
Fill with the sausage mixture.
Roll remaining pie crust to 12-inch circle; make decorative cutouts in pastry, if desired.
Place pastry over filling.
Seal and flute edges of pie. Decorate top with additional pie crust.
Cut into decorative shapes, if desired.
Beat remaining egg; brush top of pastry.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until pastry is lightly browned.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 10 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar and cocoa in saucepan; stir together.
Add milk, butter and salt; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in rolled oats, vanilla and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Slice cabbage in 1/2-inch round slices.
Cook in small amount of water until almost done.
Don't overcook.
Drain; put half of cabbage in a greased baking dish.
Cut up butter and cheese using half of each.
Spread this with half of soup, then add rest of cabbage, butter, cheese and soup.
Cover with crumbled soda crackers or bread crumbs and bake at 350° until it bubbles. Serves 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in chunks in bottom of baking dish.
Pour Veg-All over chicken.
Mix soups and chicken broth and pour over Veg-All.

title: chocolate marshmallow log
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt butter and chips until blended and melted. Remove; cool 5 minutes. Stir in marshmallows and nuts; don't let marshmallows melt. On wax paper, shape into two 7-inch rolls. Wrap in foil. Refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: bob's grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in combined dressing and steak sauce for several hours; overnight is even better. Grill over hot coals, turning as needed until done. Baste occasionally with the reserved marinade. Just before done, brush on some of your favorite barbecue sauce. Keep on grill until flavor of sauce has had chance to be absorbed into the chicken.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese, milk and pudding. Spread on cooled cake.
Put the pineapple on the cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator.

title: kids' favorite party mix
directions: After popping corn, open bag and shake pudding mix in.
Shake well.
Add graham crackers and M&M's to bag.
Shake well again. Store in airtight container.

title: brown-butter sea scallops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Pierce the potatoes in several places. Bake until tender, about 45 minutes. Halve the potatoes lengthwise and scoop the pulp into

a medium bowl. Stir in the milk, ginger, salt and pepper. Beat with an electric mixer at low speed until blended and smooth; keep warm. Heat the butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook until the butter just begins to brown slightly. Add the scallops; cook, turning once, until browned on the outside and just opaque in the center, about 1 minute on each side. Sprinkle with scallions and serve with the potatoes.

title: beef-broccoli wellington
directions: Heat
oven
In
medium
skillet, brown meat; drain well.
Add broccoli, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper. Mix
well.	Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
On
an ungreased cookie sheet, overlap long sides of 2
rectangles 1/2-inch;
firmly press edges to seal. Press or roll
to
form
a 13 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spoon meat mixture
in 3-inch
strips
lengthwise	down center of dough. Bring
long edges of dough rectangle over filling, overlapping edges slightly; pinch
edge
and
ends
to seal.
Repeat with remaining rectangles.
Brush	with beaten egg;
sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake
at
375° for 18 to 22 minutes or until deep golden brown. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and saute onion about 10 minutes or until golden.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add the chicken broth, milk, and then the broccoli. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 15-20 minutes.

title: hawaiian stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice. Combine juice and cornstarch in small bowl; stir to blend and set aside.

title: party cheddar spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except toast; mix lightly.
Spread mixture onto toast.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: grand slam popcorn balls
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, slowly heat butter and marshmallows, stirring constantly until melted and smooth.
Add food coloring if you like and stir until evenly blended.
Pour over popcorn and mix until well coated.
Form into shapes, using lightly buttered hands to protect them from the heat or press into balls using the Jolly Time popcorn ball maker or assorted molds.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In a serving bowl, combine hot macaroni and Italian salad dressing; mix well.
Cool at room temperature 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Fold in vegetables and Feta cheese.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Add brown sugar and whipping cream; microwave for 13 minutes. Stir in vanilla, pecans and butter.
Drop on buttered dish or buttered wax paper to cool.

title: saucy franks
directions: Score franks; brown in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients, except green pepper. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add peppers and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: grilled marinated shrimp and salmon fillets
directions: Gently toss all ingredients in a non-corosive container.
Allow this to marinate for several hours or overnight.
Grill salmon over hot coals until nearly done.
Now add your shrimp to the grill.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: In a small roasting pan, put a layer of sliced raw potatoes on the bottom, then a layer of thin sliced onions, then a layer of already browned beef.
Then layer the pork and beans, the tomato soup and the cream of mushroom soup.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass that has been greased and dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: saucy skillet pasta
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, spaghetti sauce mix and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together and add to first mixture.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes, then turn out on rack to finish cooling.

title: chocolate bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix water, yeast and sugar.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 3 cups flour (if using cinnamon, sift into flour).
Stir in cocoa, butter, egg and salt.
Beat until dough is very "stretchy" about 10 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and raisins, if used.
Sprinkle rest of flour on board and knead dough 5 or 6 times.
Barely incorporate flour and make a smooth round, about 1 minute.
Place dough in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise until puffy, about 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when warm. A good way to satisfy that chocolate craving without too many calories!
Per ounce:
88 calories, 2.1 g. protein, 14 g. carbohydrate, 2.8 g. fat, 9.3 mg. cholesterol, 55 mg. sodium.

title: zucchini jam
directions: In large saucepan bring to boil the zucchini and water.
Boil 6 minutes; add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Bring back to a boil and boil 6 minutes; add jello.
Bring to boil.
Boil 6 minutes, pour into sterile jars and seal.
For firm jam, keep in refrigerator.

title: gorp
directions: Empty contents into large bowl and mix until well blended. (If you like dates, coconut, banana chips or dried pineapple, add to the original mix.)
Pack into a quart-sized Ziploc bag. Travels well.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the first eight ingredients until smooth.
Stir in nuts; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: johnny cakes(makes 12 servings)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, salt and sugar.
Add boiling water; mix well, then add milk.
Heat oil in heavy large skillet over moderate heat.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls to form cakes about 3-inches in diameter.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until crisp and golden brown.
Repeat for remaining cakes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain off excess fat.
Stir in taco seasoning and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour half of cornbread mixture into well-greased pan.
Pour hamburger mixture on top and cover with remaining bread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zwieback or tweback **
directions: In a greased mixing bowl, measure 3 cups flour, salt, sugar, Carnation milk and yeast.
Mix.
Add melted butter; stir.
Add egg.
Beat by hand with a big wooden spoon for 2 minutes.
Add 3 cups of flour gradually.
Add almost 2 cups of flour or as much as needed.
Knead for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double.
Punch down.
Let rise 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in casserole.
Top with cheese, 1/2 stick
melted margarine and corn flake crumbs (about 1/2 cup).
Bake, covered, at 350° to 375° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake about 25 minutes.

title: home style grilled hamburgers
directions: Mix together lightly; shape in patties.
Grill or fry until done.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and red hots in 3 cups boiling water, stirring until they dissolve.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until set in a square 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan or gelatin mold.
Makes 9 servings.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together and put into two small loaf pans that have been sprayed with Pam.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: *May substitute with 1 cup powdered milk and 2 tablespoons nondairy creamer dissolved in 1 cup water.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Parboil scallops 2 minutes; drain, reserving 1 cup of liquid. Put scallops in a greased 2-quart casserole.
In pot, melt butter and cook onion until tender.
Add flour, then pepper, milk and liquid.
Stir until thickens; add mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Cover scallops with creamed mixture; top with American cheese, then chips.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Also good made with crabmeat or combination of seafood.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Mix cream cheese, Tabasco, soup and mayonnaise.
Soften Knox gelatine in very hot water.
Add to cheese mixture.
Blend celery, onion and shrimp into mixture.
Spray a mold with Pam.
Pour in mixture and chill overnight.
Unmold on a lettuce bed.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 48 servings (1 tablespoon each).

title: frogmore stew
directions: In large pot on stove top, add Old Bay seasoning to 2-quarts water.
Bring to a boil, add potatoes and boil again.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn and boil 10 more minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon onto a serving platter.
Serve with additional Old Bay and cocktail sauce.
Serves 12.

title: ma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Sift together next 4 ingredients, then add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.

title: german casserole
directions: Parboil the potatoes and carrots for 20 minutes. Slice potatoes thinly. Brown beef and onion. Drain excess grease; set aside.
Mix soup, catsup and mushrooms.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Layer beef-onion mixture, potatoes, soup mixture and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with onion rings and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes until onion rings are crisp and brown.
Slice the potatoes before cooking and also carrots.

title: mozzarella in carozza
directions: Heat oil.
Mix together egg, milk, cheese and seasonings. Place Mozzarella in between slices of bread and soak bread.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, celery, onion, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add chicken and rice; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cook onion, garlic and whole clove in tiny amount of water in a large heavy skillet until onion is soft. Add cut up chicken franks, capers, vinegar, diced tomato and shredded cabbage.
Stir well. Sprinkle with pepper. Add the water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake(low-fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and margarine into Bisquick until crumbly. Blend in the 1/3 cup milk. Turn onto floured surface. Knead 8 to 10 strokes. On waxed paper, roll dough to 12 x 8-inch rectangle. Turn onto greased baking sheet; remove paper. Spread preserves down center of dough. Make 2 1/2-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides. Fold strips over filling. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes. Combine sugar, milk and vanilla; drizzle over top.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Place half the bread squares on bottom.
Place half the sauteed mushrooms on bread.
Combine chopped vegetables with mayonnaise.
Spread half this mixture over the mushrooms.
Repeat layers.
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings. Pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut tops off potatoes and scoop out the centers. Mash.
Stir butter, sour cream, herbs and seasonings into mashed potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing, they mix better.
Mix with all but 1/4 cup margarine and cornflakes.
Put in
9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup
margarine
and
crushed cornflakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: drunk wieners
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in crock-pot.
Cut wieners in bite-size pieces and add to crock-pot.
Cook on low for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Melt margarine in pan and stir in flour; cook.
Add cream cheese to flour and margarine mixture after it cools a little bit. Beat the eggs; add the milk and blend.
Then add all the rest of the ingredients to the eggs and milk.

title: won tons
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except won ton skins.
Place 1 teaspoon meat mixture in center of won ton square and fold over one corner to form a triangle.
Moisten edges with water to seal.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with won ton sauce.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add.
Place 1/2 cup flour in bowl.
Add dates, candy, nuts and coconut, then add to cream mixture.
This makes
a very stiff dough.
Should be mixed with hands.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and discard.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
In mixing bowl, add remaining ingredients to softened cream cheese and blend well.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps and broil for approximately 5 minutes or until cream cheese starts to brown slightly.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Chicken breast can be deboned or cut into bite size pieces (decrease cooking time accordingly).

title: low-fat spanish chicken with rice
directions: Heat oil; brown chicken about 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to plate; season and keep warm.
Add peppers that are sliced 1/3-inch thick to skillet.
Add stock, onion and garlic.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet and heat.
Serve with Goya brand Spanish or Mexican style rice.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Fry ground beef with 1 small onion, chopped.
Drain off grease.
Combine in large saucepan rest of ingredients and cook over low heat until thick, about 2 to 3 hours.
Serve while warm. Can be frozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl mix milk and pudding; beat until it thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture.
Break up Oreo cookies and put in a blender until crushed very fine.

title: pork chop hot dish
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until heated through.

title: pineapple ham patties
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and half of the tomato sauce. Shape into patties.
Should make 6.
Pan-fry over low heat in cooking oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove from pan and set in oven to keep warm.
Fry pineapple slices until light brown.
Stir remaining tomato sauce and pineapple juice into browned bits.
Serve ham patties on pineapple slices with sauce spooned over top.

title: candy kisses(fat-free)
directions: Beat egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating continually until tips stand straight.
Gently fold in candies.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.

title: broccoli and cornbread casserole
directions: Press broccoli between 2 paper towels to absorb moisture.
Mix all together.
Pour in baking casserole dish or long baking dish. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed in mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, pumpkin, lemon juice, flour, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix, then spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Have pastry sheet sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Turn cake onto pastry sheet, spread with filling and roll cake like jelly roll.
Let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs very well.
Add sugar and continue beating until well blended.
Add oil and beat a few minutes.
Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add all sifted ingredients with zucchini, starting and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans (9 x 5-inch loaf pans) and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Check after 50 minutes.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie
directions: Combine fruit and yogurt, then fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before cutting; keep chilled in refrigerator.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and fruit, if desired.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls flat in 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and seasonings and beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Spread cheese mixture over cooled baked dough.
Then sprinkle well-drained broccoli, peppers, onion, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
One-half recipe will make 25 (2-inch) squares.

title: marinated salad
directions: Marinate all vegetables in dressing overnight.
Add cooked macaroni 4 hours before serving.

title: lebkucken
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let stand 4 days. Roll out. Cut with cookie cutters. Brush with egg white. Decorate with extra candied peel. Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: grandma billings meringue squares
directions: Let cool and spread with strawberry jam.
Then beat egg whites; add sugar, water, cornstarch and baking powder.
Spread over jam. Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs or chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Add eggs, then flour which has been sifted together with soda.
Mix good.
Roll into small balls and with wet fork flatten in a crisscross design.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir in milk, oleo and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Mixture will be thick.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt. Mix well and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is real good served with ice cream.

title: donalda tillett's beet salad
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar, water and sugar.
Dissolve Jell-O. Cool with beet juice.
Add beets, diced onion, celery and mustard seed.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and pumpkin thoroughly. Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting. Blend dry ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture, stirring until well blended. Add raisins and pecans. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12-15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 6 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix all but flour and melted butter.
This makes 2 pans.
Make a well in the 6 cups flour.
Add first mixture.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and shiny.
Let rise in warm place until double.

title: "grandma whittlesey's oatmeal cookies"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add coconut and dry ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and oatmeal; mix well. Add chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: stuffed chicken
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Place 1 slice of boiled ham, 1 slice of Swiss cheese and 2 tablespoons of stuffing on chicken.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Put chicken, seam side down, in baking dish. Cover with soup straight from the can.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave for 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Then stir in marshmallows and nuts. Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil.
Butter foil.
Chill for 30 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: chocolate nut fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 tablespoon butter. In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, milk and remaining butter. Over medium heat, bring to a full rolling boil. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows until melted. Add all the chips and unsweetened chocolate. Stir until melted. Add vanilla and nuts. Spread in a prepared pan. Cool for 1 hour at room temperature. Cut into squares and store in an airtight container (with a lock and key) in the refrigerator. This sounds awesome.

title: pizza crusts
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water and stir until dissolved. Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt. Add egg and 1 teaspoon oil. Stir until smooth and glossy. Stir in 2 more cups flour. On lightly floured surface, knead dough until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes). Place in greased bowl. Turn to grease top. Cover with towel and let rise in warm, draft-free location until dough is doubled in size (about 1 hour). Punch down dough. Chill. Divide dough in half. Pat into two greased 12 to 14-inch pizza pans (or roll out in 12-inch circles on greased cookie sheet). Crimp edges to form rims. Brush with oil. Makes 2 crusts.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain and add taco seasoning mix. Mix in beans and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread on sour cream and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle on grated cheese while hot.
Pour on salsa and serve with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a round 10 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or a 10-inch spring-form pan.
In a medium bowl, toss blueberries with lemon zest.
In a large bowl, combine
2 cups of the flour with the sugar.
Using your fingertips or a pastry blender, rub or cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Set 1 1/2 cups of the mixture aside for the crumb topping.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruits; add chilled Creamy Dressing.
Place in refrigerator and chill for several hours.

title: marinade for roast,  steak and pork chops
directions: Mix in pan; place meat inside and cover.
Allow it to marinate for 2 hours and turn over once after first hour.
This is really great with economy pork chops!

title: poke salad casserole
directions: Mix together; put Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until done.
Good.
Good.
Good!

title: chocolate cream frosting
directions: Stir together and spread over cool cake.

title: rice with cinnamon
directions: Heat rice, water and salt to boiling in 3-quart saucepan, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 12 to 14 minutes.
(Do not lift cover or stir.)
Remove from heat.
Fluff rice lightly with fork.
Cover and let steam 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in margarine and powdered sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: greenbriar hotel pumpkin cake
directions: In large mixing bowl beat eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Blend in oil, then pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or into two 9-inch prepared cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Bake longer if necessary, especially if using a tube pan (approximately 1 hour).
Remove from oven and partially cool on rack.
Remove cake from pans and allow to cool completely before frosting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs on top of casserole before baking.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add all together in a Dutch oven or slow cooker.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: cornell sauce(for barbecue chicken)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg and add to mixture. Marinate for 5 to 6 hours.
Covers 4 to 5 halves.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Make chocolate cake as directed.
While hot, poke lots of holes in cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and Hershey's chocolate syrup; pour over hot cake.
Put in fridge until cool.
Then add Cool Whip. Crush Heath bars and put over top of cake.
Leave in fridge.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Mix egg and dry ingredients and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
A half hour before serving roast, drain 1/2 cup drippings from pan; place in 8 x 8-inch pan. Increase oven to 400° and place pudding mix on top of drippings. Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices after buttering. Spread with cooked chicken, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread on top of chicken in pan.
Combine eggs, milk and salt; pour over all.
Mix soups and pimento plus 1/4 cup milk and spread over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with crumbs the last 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before eating.

title: imitation "crab" cakes
directions: In a large bowl mix zucchini, Stove Top stuffing, egg and seasoning.
Make into patties.
Fry in skillet with oil until golden brown on both sides.
Remove patties and put onto paper toweled plate.
Serve plain or on buns.
Tastes like crab cakes but there is no crab added.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together until sugar is dissolved.
(The recipe will make sauce for up to 3 pounds of chicken wings.) Remove tips from wings and cut wings in two pieces.
Marinate chicken wings in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: okra bacon salad
directions: Combine bacon, okra, onion and green pepper in large bowl. Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Blend well.
Pour over vegetables. Toss gently to coat.

title: goulash
directions: Drain beef.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until tender. Season to taste.
Best in summer straight from garden.

title: charcoal grilled white fish
directions: Make 4 or 5 shallow slits on each side of fish.
Brush fish generously with a mixture of oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper, oregano and Accent.
Cook over coals until golden brown, brushing with mixture.
Turn fish gently to cook both sides.
When fish is done, put on serving platter and pour remaining mixture over fish. Serves 3 to 4.

title: quiche
directions: Make pie crust.
Brown onions.
Set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and set aside.
Beat 4 eggs; add cream.
Put cheese, onions and bacon in pie crust.
Pour cream mixture over top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: stuffed wiener rolls
directions: Grind Spam into bowl.
Add eggs, mustard, pickle, catsup and cheese.
Mix well.
Brush halves of buns with melted margarine. Divide meat mixture onto buns and spread evenly.
Close buns and warp each in square of foil.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 10 hot sandwiches.

title: "reese's" peanut butter bars
directions: Soften margarine.
Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the Hershey bar with a little milk and spread on top of the dry mixture.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a loaf pan with aluminum foil. Cream shortening and sugar; add mashed bananas and beaten eggs, 1 at a time, then add vanilla, dry ingredients and nuts. Pour into the foil-lined pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let set 5 minutes and remove cake from pan by lifting the foil. Remove foil from bread and place on a cooling rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook
squash in salted water until tender.
Drain well. Add pimento,
soup, onion, carrots, sour cream and egg.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo in pan.
Add stuffing; mix well.
Line 2 quart baking dish with this, but keep some for topping.
Pour squash mixture over
stuffing
and sprinkle remaining over top.
Dot with butter on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: streusel-filled coffee cake
directions: Mix together with a fork before mixing coffee cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to thread spinning stage.
Add peanuts.
Cook until candy is a golden brown and peanuts have popped (about 10 minutes).
Remove from fire and add baking soda. Stir thoroughly, but quickly and pour immediately onto well-greased surface such as marble or porcelain.
When cold, slice knife or spatula underneath edges, popping candy up.
Break into pieces by hitting on back side with knife.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cocoa mix
directions: In a bowl, with a lid, mix all ingredients together.
Secure with lid.
When ready to use, fill a cup or glass about 1/4 full of cocoa mix.
Pour hot water over cocoa and stir until mixed.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt together.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then with hands, squeeze out all water.
Boil together for 1 minute sugar, vinegar, water, celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix all together. Can be used immediately or placed in containers and frozen.

title: cream pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with other ingredients and press into pie pan.
Reserve some crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, add 2 teaspoons of the mix to one cup of hot water.
This is a good cold weather drink.

title: gelatin punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water and ginger ale.
Serve over generous amount of ice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay dough end to end on pizza pan; press and bake according to directions.
Mix together cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix. Spread on pizza, then top with your favorite chopped vegetables. Cut and enjoy!

title: sharon's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare mushrooms.
Chop stems.
Spray pan.
Add garlic.
Cook over low heat (covered).
Add chopped stems and some white wine or you can use a little margarine if you don't have white wine. Cover, cook on low until tender.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients on low speed until crumbly.
Press into pan 2 2/3 cups crumb mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
In another bowl add rest of ingredients.
Blend well, and spoon evenly over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with cream or Cool Whip.

title: browned rice
directions: In a skillet, brown rice, stirring often until lightly browned. Turn into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish; add water and stir with a fork to separate rice grains. Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Meanwhile in a skillet, over low heat, melt butter; add onion and mushrooms and saute until onions are transparent. Remove from heat and add water chestnuts and soy sauce. Add rice and blend gently. Return to casserole. Bake uncovered 15 minutes.

title: sour cream salmon with asparagus
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add chopped asparagus, onion and bell pepper. Cook 6 minutes; stir occasionally. Spoon into bowl and set aside. Wipe skillet dry with paper towel.

Re-coat with cooking spray. Rub white pepper on both sides of salmon. Add to skillet. Add white wine and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes or until salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork. Place salmon on a serving platter. Reserve cooking liquid.
Spoon asparagus mixture around salmon. Cover and keep warm.
Bring reserved cooking liquid to a boil.
Cook until reduced to 1 tablespoon.
Remove from heat. Cool slightly.
Stir in yogurt, sour cream, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Spoon over salmon and asparagus mixture.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Beat egg well.
Add milk and melted oleo.
Add this to flour mixture.
Stir just enough to combine (do not overmix).
Fold in diced peaches.
Pour batter into greased tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all together and spread evenly on each tortilla.
Roll up. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, slice diagonally.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled layer.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over the previous layers.
Spread the remainder of the Cool Whip.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing.
Spread on a slice of ham, then layer ham and mixture.
Spread until you use 5 slices of ham. Roll and chill.
Slice and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: cowboy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Mix in oats and chocolate chips.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.

title: quick quiche
directions: Beat together eggs and cottage cheese.
Layer in uncooked pie crust, egg mixture, cheese, mushrooms and more egg mixture, ending with cheese and egg mixture.
Sprinkle well with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Beat until fluffy.
Stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients (if more flour is needed, add until a nice cookie consistency).
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix well on medium speed of mixer.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Then line with wax paper.
Pour mix onto it.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
No longer!
Sprinkle a linen towel with powdered sugar.
Flip hot cake onto it then pull off wax paper. While the cake is still hot, roll top to bottom like for nut roll. Let cool.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas; mix.
Add dry ingredients and beat for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: nacho skillet dinner
directions: Heat 12 inch non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Brown beef. Drain and set aside. To same skillet add peppers, onions, and galic; cook until softened. Stir in beans, tomatoes, seasoning, and reserved beef. Cook, stirring, until bubbly. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover, reduce heat to low. Cook until cheese melts. serve with tortilla chips.

title: ruby red fruit punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; add this to 1 1/2 quarts cold water and remaining ingredients.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan for this dessert.
Have 1 layer of graham crackers in the pan.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Put half of mixture on top of layer of graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Put the rest of pudding on the graham crackers.
Put on 3rd layer of graham crackers.
Add the frosting to complete the dessert.
I buy prepared frosting.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut up and skin chicken.
Place in rectangular baking pan and add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, steak sauce and honey in a bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Return to oven for 10 minutes, basting with sauce occasionally.
Remove and top chicken with pineapple slices.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken to serve.
(Can be served on a bed of rice.)

title: squash muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Cream butter and sugar; stir in molasses until well blended.
Beat in egg and squash.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir into egg and squash mixture.
Add pecans.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: "millie's" chicken enchilada
directions: Poach or bake chicken or turkey and cut up.
Mix all ingredients together, reserving a handful of cheese for top.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved cheese; cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: low-fat chocolate ice cream
directions: You can substitute any flavor instant pudding.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Add cream (I use Carnation milk); alternate with flour, sifted.
Add flavoring.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then turn oven down to 300° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Dissolve yeast in potato water. Stir in buttermilk. Add flour and salt. Cover and let stand overnight in a warm place.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix together with the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Fold in the nuts and apples.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in oven or microwave.
Cool and cut in half lengthwise.
Saute onions and garlic in 1/2 stick margarine until onions are tender.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving a thin shell. Combine all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.
You may need to add a small amount of milk.
Stuff back into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and toss in bag with sugar and cinnamon. Layer in a greased tube pan.
Melt brown sugar and oleo and drizzle over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then turn out on platter.

title: sweet tator muffins
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a bowl.
Combine milk and next four ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Add raisins.
Spoon batter into muffin pans coated with Pam, 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Check doneness by placing toothpick in center of muffin until toothpick dry.
Remove from pans immediately.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cucumber-lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in enamelware for 12 hours or overnight.
Remove sliced cucumbers from lime water.
Discard lime water; rinse 3 times in fresh cold water. Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water.

title: garden tuna casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, flour and seasonings in large saucepan; gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium heat until thickened.
Add tuna, 1 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together (except croutons).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with croutons over top.
Mix croutons in some melted butter.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: famous amos cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: wake up drink
directions: Blend ingredients; pour and drink.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown all meat together. When browned, put in slow cooker. Add Velveeta cheese in chunks. Add Ro-Tel. When cheese is melted, serve with tortilla chips.

title: spicy sauerkraut
directions: Mix and season according to taste.
Let season in the refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add corn syrup and beat.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
This makes 1 crust right in pie.
The pecans will rise to the top and form topping.

title: rice pudding
directions: In crock-pot or slow cooker, combine the milk, rice, salt and sugar. Stir and cover. Cook for 3 hours or longer.
Mix together remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix for 2 round cake pans, according to package directions.

title: pear preserves
directions: Combine sugar and water; cook rapidly 2 minutes. Add pears and boil gently for 15 minutes. Add remaining sugar and lemon, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cook rapidly until fruit is clear, about 25 minutes. Cover and let stand 12 to 24 hours in a cool place. Pack fruit into hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Cook syrup 3 to 5 minutes or longer if too thin. Pour, boiling hot, over fruit, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps. Process half pints and pints 20 minutes at 180° to 185° in
hot water bath. Yield: About 5 half pints.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Place pork, water, ginger and soy in a pan; bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Drain and let cool.
Prepare Sweet-Sour Sauce and set aside.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Put roast in pan; cover with soups and dry soup and wine. Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not remove.
Cover until finished.

title: mexican stromboli
directions: In large skillet, cook turkey and drain.
Stir in half of the beans and all of the salsa.
Mash the remaining beans with fork or potato masher and add to meat mixture.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, until liquid has evaporated.

title: marinated broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Use a large bowl.
Fix broccoli and cauliflower into small flower heads.
Cut mushrooms in half.
Mix mayo, sugar and wine vinegar together.
Pour over vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.
Enjoy.

title: purple cow shakes
directions: Pour the juice concentrate and 1 cup milk into blender container.
Scoop in 2 cups ice cream.
Cover and blend on high speed 30 seconds.
Serve right away.

title: bob's salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, onion and 2 tablespoons vinegar. Mix well with blender. Add oil very slowly, beating constantly. This will become very thick. Add remaining vinegar and lemon juice. Continue beating until thick. Stir in celery seed. Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: double chocolate butter cakes
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well with mixer.
Set aside.

title: seafaring salmon salad
directions: Sprinkle salmon with lemon juice.
Stir in eggs, pickle, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine sugar
with evaporated milk, salt, marshmallows and 1/2 cup margarine in
a saucepan and heat over medium heat until it comes to a
boil.
Boil	5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cherry
flavored
chips	and 1 teaspoon margarine. Add peanut butter and	peanuts.
Spread
over cherry layer and chill.	Cut into squares.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes, cut each in half lengthwise.
Then cut into even wedges.
Boil wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain and pat dry.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve as a snack or with hamburgers.

title: cheesy olive appetizers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Spread olive mixture evenly over cut side of muffin halves.
Place muffin halves on an un-greased baking sheet.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat (with oven door partially opened) for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut each muffins half into quarters and serve immediately.

title: candy orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together 3 times.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk.
Stir other ingredients into batter with spoon.
Add orange slices with last ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours in greased and floured tube pan.

title: deviled egg filling
directions: Slice eggs in half.
Mash egg yolks; set aside.
Combine vinegar, butter, sugar, salt and pepper in a 2 cup measure bowl. Microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/4 minutes or until boiling. Stir in mashed egg yolks and slaw dressing until smooth.
Fill each egg white half with a heaping tablespoonful of filling.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar
and
sugar;
pour over vegetables. Toss to mix.
Crumble bacon on top just before serving.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, eggs, pineapple, cubed bread and milk. Mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Mix melted butter with flour.
Add broth and milk.
Stir over medium heat until smooth.
Add cheese sauce until smooth, then add beer.

title: tasso and oysters in cream on pasta
directions: Combine the hot water,	oil and salt in a large pot and bring to a
boil.
Cook spaghetti, uncovered, (about 4 minutes for fresh spaghetti
and
7 minutes if dry).	Do not overcook. When done, immediately
wash
spaghetti
with	cold
water and drain in a colander.
After
cooled, pour a liberal amount of oil
on	your hands
and	toss
spaghetti.
Set
aside.
Heat serving plates in a 250° oven.

title: onion topped pot roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Coat a Dutch oven with vegetable cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot. Add roast; brown on all sides.
Remove roast from pan; sprinkle with pepper and set roast aside.
Wipe drippings from pan with paper towel.

title: butter-pecan dessert
directions: Mix together into a crumb.
Sprinkle in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken-beef supreme
directions: Put dried beef slices on bottom of shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Wrap chicken breast halves with 1/2 strip bacon and place on top of dried beef.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken soup with sour cream until mixture is smooth and well-blended.
Pour over chicken breasts.

title: bourbon pecan pie with hard sauce
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Beat eggs for 30 seconds and slowly; add syrup until blended.
Stir in melted butter, bourbon and pecans.
Pour filling into baked pie shell and return to oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool and serve with hard sauce.

title: mango bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add dates and sugar to butter.
Stir and cook
until mixture thickens and turns dark brown (3 to 5 minutes).
After mixture boils, add vanilla.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Cool slightly and form into small balls.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Arrange chicken in pan.
In a small bowl or 2-cup measuring cup, mix all other ingredients together.

Pour all of the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Baste with sauce as needed if chicken appears dry as it bakes. (After chicken is finished, skim away excess fat). Excellent served with broccoli or some other green vegetable along with rice, mashed potatoes or buttered noodles.

title: mixed fruit tart with amaretto creme
directions: Let pie crust sit for 20 minutes at room temperature.
On floured surface, roll pastry to 11-inch circle and press into 9-inch spring-form pan with 1-inch up the sides of the pan.
Flute edge of pastry and with fork, prick sides and bottom.
Line pastry shell with a double thickness of foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Remove foil and brush pastry with milk, then sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes more.
Cool.

title: lemon-garlic chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for marinade.
Marinate chicken overnight (or all day).
Cook chicken on grill, basting with marinade.
Or you may broil or bake chicken in oven, as you would normally do chicken.
Bake at 400 for about 30 to 40 minutes. Baste as desired.

title: german pineapple cheesecake
directions: Cream together margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, egg, 1 1/2 cups flour and baking powder.
Then spread this mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan and then press down.
Next add pineapple on top.
Then blend the cream cheese, 1 1/2 tablespoons flour, eggs, milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over the pineapple.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: scalloped mushrooms
directions: Place layer of uncooked mushrooms in a buttered shallow casserole.
Scatter half of stuffing over them.
Repeat with another layer of mushrooms and top with remainder of stuffing. Place a few mushroom caps, gill side up, on top with a bit of butter inside. Pour cream and stock over the top.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Before serving, remove foil. Turn mushrooms on top, right side up, and cook a few minutes longer.
Pour sherry over at the very last. Serves 8.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heavily butter the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and oleo in microwave for approximately 2 minutes.
Blend in powdered sugar until smooth and pour over cake mix.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 150°.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli and onion to large pan.
Cover with 3 cups of water and add chicken bouillon cubes.
Boil until tender.
Do not drain.
In a small saucepan, add margarine, flour and canned milk. Heat on low heat; add cream cheese to mixture and melt into sauce. When sauce is well blended, add to broccoli mixture.
Stir well and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish. Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin burgers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes, mixing well.

title: spinach dip and hawaiian bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup mix, sour cream and mayo.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Cover and chill.
To serve, scoop out the center of the round Hawaiian bread and tear into bite size pieces for dipping.
Fill the center of the bread with the dip and arrange the pieces of bread around the outside.
Can also be served with rye bread, if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw hamburger in bottom of greased casserole or roaster; add onion and mixed vegetables.
Mix soups and water and add.
On top, put Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Pour pineapple in bottom of oblong pan or dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix next.
