Dot all over with pats of butter.
Top with pecans.
Bake uncovered at 350° until golden brown.

title: easy oven browned potatoes
directions: Melt butter and stir in onion soup mix.
Roll potatoes in mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture over potatoes.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake 1 hour at 400° until potatoes are easily pierced with fork.
Stir occasionally.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Cook beans per package instructions, cooking until most liquid is gone.
Brown onion and garlic in bacon grease.
Brown hamburger; add tomato paste and tomato sauce or Ro-Tel and chili powder.
Cook slow for 20 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 25 or 30 minutes.
May add water if needed.
Beans need to be thick when served.
Taco sauce may be added.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion, drain fat.
Put meat mixture in stew pot and add beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Stir.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Pour on top of Fritos and sprinkle with cheese.

title: glazed chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rice, water and scallions in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cranberry sauce, French dressing and onion soup.
Using 1/3 of mixture, put several spoonfuls over rice mixture.
Arrange chicken breasts on top.
Spoon remaining cranberry mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: taffy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and water until it reaches hard ball stage.
Stir as mixture cooks.
Remove from heat and add soda, butter and vanilla.
Stir only enough to mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan.
When taffy becomes cool enough to handle, pull until it becomes a light color.
Stretch into long ropes and cut into small pieces.

title: six-layer mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Mix with mayonnaise, garlic, salt and lemon juice.
Spread on bottom of dish.
Spread sour cream.
Pour on picante sauce.
Mix olives and tomatoes and place on top of picante sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top and chill.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar, but do not boil.
Add while warm rest of ingredients and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: toffee candy
directions: Put butter (margarine), sugar and nuts in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil and stir constantly until thermometer reaches 300° (hard crack).
Pour into cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Top immediately with Hershey bars and spread when melted over the toffee mixture.
Refrigerate.
Chop into bite size pieces and refrigerate to store.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together in double boiler.
Mix eggs and sugar together until light in color.
Slowly stir in melted chocolate mixture, then stir in flour.
Add walnuts, if desired. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll
out
crescent
rolls
onto
pizza pan.
Brown and drain sausage.
Add on top of crust, then thawed hash browns. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until browned, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk-lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan.
Gradually add buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Add cream cheese; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon rind, juice, butter and 1 teaspoon lemon extract.
Spoon into pie shells.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar with electric mixer on high for 1 minute.
Gradually add powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Beat in lemon extract.
Spread meringue over filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, browning top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bachelor's pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and nutmeg. Combine flour, salt and
soda; add alternately with buttermilk. Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into prepared tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter on top; cover with cheese.
Top with paprika.
Bake in oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
If cheese starts to get too brown, cover with foil.
Serves 10 to 12.
Can be frozen.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Drain and mix with remainder of ingredients and cook slowly.

title: banana split pie
directions: If not using prepared crust, cover the bottom and sides of pie
pan
with
margarine-crumb mixture.
Spread the other ingredients in the order listed.
Chill before serving.

title: beef stew supreme
directions: The above ingredients should be place in the crock-pot in the order given. Stir several times; cover and cook.

title: calzone
directions: Make crust, following directions on package. While dough is rising, mix cheeses, egg and other fillings, as desired.
Make circle of half of dough. Add filling. Put other half of dough circle on top.
Pinch edges together. Sprinkle top with water and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in the bottom of
a turkey roaster.
Bake in 250° oven until the nuts are toasted, stirring often.
Takes about 1 hour.

title: pink fizz
directions: Stir together concentrate, wine and 2 bottles carbonated beverage in an airtight container; cover and freeze 8 hours or until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes; place in a punch bowl.
Add remaining bottle carbonated beverage, stirring until slushy.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into walnut sized balls.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
These are good hot or cold.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Put cut up chicken and onions into water and cook slowly until tender; add salt.
Remove chicken, cut meat into small (1-inch) pieces and return to broth together with corn, which has been cut from the cob, celery, pinch of salt, 1 egg and a little milk.
Mix well with fork and fingers to form small crumbs.
Drop these into the soup; also, the chopped, hard-boiled eggs.
Boil for 15 minutes or longer.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into desired size greased bread pans, making sure they are only 1/2 to 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick; drop on a greased sheet at desired size.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cut sliced apples into bite size pieces. Place in baking dish and cover with grated cheese. Crumble next 3 ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut Crisco in with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk; mix well.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead lightly a few times.
Roll to a 1/2 inch thickness.
Place on greased pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix zwieback, 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Put all but approximately 1/4 cup on sides and bottom of spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and eggs (one at a time).
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into zwieback-lined pan.
Sprinkle mixture over top of cake.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Allow cake to remain one hour more.
Cool and serve.
Refrigerate.

title: simple kosher pickles
directions: Tie
spices
in
a
cheesecloth;
in
a large pot.
Add liquids,
salt,
sugar and tied-up spices.	Mix and simmer for 15 minutes
over
medium
heat.
Cut cucumbers into quarters; pack into
the
jars (4 quart jars or 8 pint jars).
Into each jar add 1 clove garlic, 1 to 2 pieces red pepper, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed and 1 bay leaf.
Fill each jar with liquid.
Hot water
bath for
minutes or just keep in refrigerator for crunchiness.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water in 1 1/2 - 2 quart dish and allow to cool some before adding other ingredients.	Soften cream cheese and blend with Dream Whip (made according to pkg. directions) on high speed of electric mixer.
Add fruit, nuts, coconut, cream cheese mixture to the cool gelatin, stirring well.
Chill several hours until set.	Different Jell-O and fruit choices are:
cherry Jell-O with pineapple and cherries; lime Jell-O with pineapple; strawberry Jell-O with strawberries and bananas; orange Jell-O with oranges and pineapple; orange Jell-O with mandarin oranges.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Slit pockets in chops.
Cook onion and pepper in butter.
Mix corn, crumbs and seasonings in bowl.
Pour onion mixture over; mix lightly.
Stuff chops.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: special salmon steaks
directions: Place salmon or halibut on lightly greased 8 inch square baking dish; top with butter and lemon juice.
Combine onion, parsley, garlic salt and lemon pepper, and sprinkle over fish. Bake uncovered at 400° for 15-20 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 2.

title: mustard hamburger sandwich
directions: Scramble hamburger and fry in frying pan until brown.
Drain off all grease.
Add mustard.
Add salt and pepper; place on hamburger bun and serve.
Use more or less of mustard if desired.

title: tea punch
directions: Steep tea in boiling water for 5 minutes with spices.
Strain and cool.
Add juices and sugar.
Pour into ice-filled punch bowl. Garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: homemade maple syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a 1-quart saucepan; add sugar and maple flavoring, stirring to dissolve.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Leftover syrup may be stored in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts in deep foil lined pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: basil chicken
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat in skillet. Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Cook chicken 5 minutes on each side.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes until juices run
clear.
Serve with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.
Something a little different for dinner!

title: shrimp stroganoff(serves 2 to 4 persons)
directions: In saucepan, cook onion
with
garlic
in
butter until tender.
Blend in soup and	sour
cream until smooth.
Stir in water, shrimp and parsley.	Put
lid on and heat until bubbly, stirring often.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Beat eggs in a bowl until fluffy.
Add cooking oil, sugar and defrosted strawberries.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt into a mixing bowl.
Add strawberry mixture and mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out of pans and cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves. This bread slices best when chilled.
May be sliced and warmed to serve with butter for breakfast or brunch or sliced thinly, spread with whipped cream cheese and serve with fruit salad for lunch or used to make tea sandwiches.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Boil water in large saucepan.
Add 3 cups uncooked macaroni.
Boil until tender; drain.
Add hamburger mixture to macaroni.
Also add the chopped stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, then add sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over vegetables.

title: parmesan-garlic popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, parsley and dill; sprinkle over popcorn and toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Grind meat and onion together three times.
Add egg, potatoes, seasoning and milk.
Mix well and form into small balls.
Brown on all sides in heavy skillet.
Remove meat balls and add water and flour.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Place meat balls and gravy in casserole and bake 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: chocolate laced pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry; crimp or flute crust. Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie crusts.
Pecans may be in batter or spread on top of pies.
Bake until brown and firm, 30 or 40 minutes, at 350°, then reduce to 300° for 15 minutes until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together; shape into balls (about golf ball size).
Brown in skillet, turning so not to burn.
Drain and serve with sauce or gravy.

title: lemon ice punch
directions: Combine water and sugar in a pan; boil for 5 minutes.
Let stand and cool.
Add lemon juice.
Freeze in ice trays or mold 2 or 3 days in advance.
When ready to serve, add ice mixture to the pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Serves 30.
Use medium punch bowl.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Pat dry rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Lay chicken on top (I take off the skin).
Sprinkle onion soup mix over it. Spread mushroom soup and drained mushrooms on the top.
Pour milk over all ingredients and cover with lid or foil.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together.
Sift the next 5 ingredients together; add to mixture.
Stir in zucchini and nuts or seeds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fresh berry cobbler
directions: Toss berries with sugar and lemon juice.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Combine biscuit mix, melted margarine, egg and milk.
Mix lightly with fork.
Drop dough over fruit. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 400° oven in a 10 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Serve warm.

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Combine the sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Let boil on low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the nuts and stir just until they are well coated.
Pour onto waxed paper and quickly separate the nuts with two forks.
Store in airtight container.
Great to give as a homemade gift.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and pour into well-greased baking pan and sprinkle batter with brown sugar, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy
saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed
milk
and
egg
yolks.
Cook
and stir until thickened and
bubbly.
Remove
from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Arrange sliced bananas on bottom of pie shell.
Pour
filling over bananas;
cover them.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread whipped topping on pie.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt
butter, cream cheese, milk and pepper over medium heat until creamy.
Pour corn and cream cheese mixture in dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: delightful four
directions: First Layer:
Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan in the oven.
Add 3/4 cup chopped nuts (sprinkle evenly in the bottom of pan).
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook the sugar, salt, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add Jell-O and few drops of red food coloring.
Partly chill.
Pour fresh strawberries (capped and washed) into baked pastry shell. Pour cooked mixture over berries.
Chill well.
Top with whipped cream.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend egg, milk and salad oil. Add dry ingredients all at once to wet ingredients and mix until moistened.
Stir in apple strips.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion and peppers.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add rice and simmer 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: In large pot, bring water, salt and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add torsk.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain carefully.
Pat torsk dry with paper towel and place on foil-lined broiler pan or 15 x 18-inch jelly roll pan.
Butter generously and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 3 to 4 inches for 5 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve immediately with melted butter. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veal steak and batter
directions: Place the veal steak in a greased baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put pats of butter over the steak.
Mix the flour, eggs, baking powder, pinch of salt and milk to make a thin batter.
Pour over the steak and place in a hot oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until brown.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: burger bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Uncover and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: crab and shrimp croquettes
directions: Mix together shrimp, crabmeat, potatoes, salt, pepper, egg, parsley and lemon juice.
This should be a fairly dry mixture that can be easily shaped into a croquette.
Refrigerate shaped croquettes at least an hour.
Roll croquette in flour, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat fat to 375° in deep kettle.
Put in a few croquettes so they will have room to brown evenly on all sides. Cook about 3 minutes each.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.
Makes 12 croquettes.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix the horseradish, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar and mustard in a small bowl and add a pinch of salt.
Whip the cream until it is stiff and fold it into the other ingredients.
Chill until needed. It is a good idea to chill horseradish sauce for at least 3 hours before serving.
Serve with hot or cold roast beef.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook beef in large skillet over medium high heat until browned, stirring to separate meat; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms, onion and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Romano cheese, egg and spinach in medium bowl.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups of meat sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place a layer of noodles and 1/2 cheese mixture and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers of sauce, noodles and cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake in preheated oven 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans, 1 egg and margarine together. Batter will be very stiff. Pat with your fingertips into a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.

title: tempting turkey casserole
directions: Combine cheese spread and milk; mix well. Toss warm spaghetti with margarine. Combine all ingredients; mix well. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Cover; bake at 350° until hot, 30 to 35 minutes. Stir before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: lo-cal thousand island dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in food processor.
Stir in remaining ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cut shortening in dry ingredients as for pie crust.
Beat together eggs, sugar, milk and flavoring.
Stir into dry ingredients and chill overnight.
Roll out and cut in favorite holiday shapes; Christmas, Easter, Valentines, etc.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: husband's pleasing dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine.
Combine with flour and pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup topping. Spread over cooled crust. Combine instant pudding with milk. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread balance of topping over pudding.

title: homemade bread
directions: Let raise twice in pan.
Put in bread pans and let raise.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Following directions on pkg add taco seasoning mix.
Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a 9x13 dish.
Mix salsa, olives, chili powder, pepper and part of the cheese.
Then add this mixture to the meat.
Pour over the cream cheese. Sprinkle the rest of the grated cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: spaghetti baked
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Brown hamburger.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Put in casserole dish, then top with hamburger, onion, green pepper mixture.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour over hamburger.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Pour into mold.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together until onion is transparent. Add potato buds, making a very stiff mashed potato mixture.
Add sour cream and cheese; combine well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish steak
directions: Put in an oblong baking dish or crock-pot the cut up steak. Put on top of steak the cut up onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Then put the whole jar of sauce on top of the mixture. Cover and bake 2 hours at 350° or in the crock-pot for 4 hours. Good, easy, delicious and tender.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Mix salad dressing, sugar and water together.
Sift dry ingredients; combine with mixture; then add vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven until done, 350°.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Spread sliced tomatoes with mustard.
Place one thin slice cheese and cracker crumbs sauteed in butter on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 300°.
Put under broiler for a short time before serving.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients two minutes. Pour into 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 75 to 80 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Toss apples with 1/2 cup of white flour and set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine white flour (remaining), whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar, baking powder, salt and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add oil, milk and egg whites; stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in apples.
Pour batter into a 10-inch round baking pan (nonstick).
Take the remaining brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over coffee.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pork chops supper
directions: In bottom of baking dish, pour 1 can chicken and rice soup over uncooked rice.
Prepare pork chops for cooking.
Place pork chops over rice.
Sprinkle paprika over pork chops.
Scatter mushrooms over rice and pork chops.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill and serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: grandma a's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Serve on tossed salad.

title: western lottas
directions: Roll each wiener in a tortilla and place in bottom of well oiled baking dish. Blend chili, onion and tomato sauce and pour over wieners. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter real well.
Blend in other ingredients. Pour the filling into two uncooked pie shells and bake at 350° until firm.
This recipe makes two large pies.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add Jell-O, cream cheese and apricot nectar.
Pour in 8 x 14-inch dish.
When partially set, fold in pecans, celery and Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator to set.
Makes a large dish.

title: eggless wacky cake
directions: Place all ingredients in an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Stir with a fork until completely mixed.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°. Cool in pan on rack.
Frost as desired.

title: easy punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl and pour drinks over it.

title: engelbert humperdinck's special scalloped chicken(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter and saute almonds until golden.
Stir in soup mix blended with flour and milk.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer 1 cup potatoes, 1 cup chicken and 1 cup carrots.
Pour 1/2 sauce over layers.
Repeat with remaining potatoes, chicken and carrots.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: martha's spaghetti salad
directions: Toss and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss frequently.

title: peanut butter surprise
directions: Mix honey, rice cereal, dry milk and peanut butter into bowl. Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Spread coconut on waxed paper.
Shape mix into small balls and roll in the coconut on all sides.
Place on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour and serve.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add the rest.
Press with hands into an ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until dough springs back when lightly touched with fingers.
Cut while warm in pan.

title: triple layer chocolate cake
directions: *Buttermilk can be made by adding 1 tablespoon of vinegar to milk.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and beat well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican style rice
directions: Place a small amount of cooking oil into a frying pan.
Place uncooked rice, onion and green pepper in pan also.

Fry on medium high heat, stirring constantly, until rice turns a white color. Add cut up, canned tomatoes, water and spices; stir and simmer, uncovered, on medium heat until rice is tender, approximately 20 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.
Shape dough into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice thinly and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add egg yolks and milk to dry mixture in heavy pan.
Mix until free of lumps.
Add margarine in small pieces.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Spoon pie filling over pie.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine ingredients and dip hot dog into batter.
Drop into hot grease.

title: un-beet-able relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except beets.
Mix well.
Add beets; toss to mix.
Serve chilled with grilled meats and sandwiches.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and egg, then dry ingredients, milk, vanilla, rhubarb and nuts.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: marinated roast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well and place roast in a shallow dish.
Pour marinade over roast.
Cover; marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator, turning once.
Bake roast in marinade at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Serve with pan drippings.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice across grain into 3 x 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.
Combine soy sauce, sherry and garlic.
Mix well.
Add steak and marinate for 30 minutes.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Saute garlic in 2 tablespoons of olive oil until fragrant. Add onions, carrots and chopped spinach leaves.
Toss and saute until al dente; remove from pan.
Mix ground beef mixture (3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, 3 tablespoons bread crumbs, parsley and egg).
Form into small meat balls.
Brown in pan with remaining tablespoon of olive oil.
When brown on all sides and firm, add vegetables, cooked noodles and chicken broth.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: cherry pie squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar in large bowl. Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract. Blend in flour. Pour half of batter in prepared dish. Top with cherry pie filling, then pour remaining batter over. Bake until golden and firm to touch. Cool slightly in pan. Cut into squares. Serve warm or at room temperature. Makes about 12 servings.

title: garlic dressing
directions: In a covered container, combine all ingredients.
Cover and shake well to mix.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Boil milk, butter and sugar (stirring constantly) over medium heat to 236° to 238° (use candy thermometer), then remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and morsels.
Stir thoroughly.
Add extract flavorings.
Stir again.
Pour into an ungreased pan, preferably 11 x 15 x 1/2-inch.
Let cool and harden for 8 to 12 hours.
Cut into desired size pieces.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Mix 1 cup margarine and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add sugar, water, flour, eggs, 1/2 cup milk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour onto greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: granny's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and soda to flour; sift again.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, adding sour cream.
Add thawed coconut, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° until done (about 1 hour and 15 minutes) or until toothpick inserted into cake comes out clean.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add cauliflowerets and cook, covered, over low heat 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen peas, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer, separating peas with fork if necessary.
Stir in chopped pimiento. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Bring syrup to a boil.
Slice and pack pickles in jars.
Add 1/2 teaspoon dill seed to each quart.
Pour syrup over pickles. Process 5 minutes in boiling water after boiling point is reached. Yields 6 to 7 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Cut up and place in 8 x 12 casserole dish. Mix together soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Crush up Ritz crackers and put on top. Cook 30 minutes on 350 degrees.

title: cauliflower scallop
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over cauliflower. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-n-drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in oil, vanilla and rind.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into oil mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until a delicate brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peach preserves
directions: Cook for 15 minutes until boiling the peaches, pineapple and sugar.
Then add peach jello.
Place in clean jelly jar and seal with lids or paraffin wax.

title: saw mill gravy
directions: In a black skillet, put margarine.
Let melt over low heat. When melted, add a little flour and sausage patties, that have been cooked, drained and chopped, but do not let flour brown.
You want this to be a white gravy.
Mix and add half water and milk to make gravy as thick or thin as you like.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Add to cooked carrots, chopped pepper and sliced onions. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots while still warm.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas with fork.
In a mixing bowl, combine bananas, sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add the flour, soda, salt and last, add the sour milk. Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Cover wheat with water at least 15 minutes.
Drain and squeeze out excess.
Chop vegetables fine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with wheat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Kraft Zesty Italian dressing. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Keeps well several days.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in molasses, egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Refrigerate dough for 3 hours.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread in 12 x 17 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook limas according to package directions; add soup, cheese and pimentos.
Place in casserole.
Cover with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: walnut tarts
directions: Combine margarine and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill.
Divide dough into 24 balls. Press into miniature muffin pan.
Fill each cup 3/4 full of brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put dill in jars (the amount you like).
Place nice pickling size cucumbers in jars.
Heat water, vinegar and salt to a boil. Pour over cucumbers.
Set in hot water bath just long enough for cucumbers to change color and hot enough to seal.

title: *fillings for lenten pitas
directions: In a large saucepan or skillet, saute onions in oil, then add balance of ingredients. Cook until rice is cooked. Cool before using.

title: instant hot spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and store in a tightly covered jar. When ready to use, put one heaping tablespoonful in a cup and fill with boiling water.
Stir and serve.

title: peach melba shortcake
directions: In medium bowl, sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over peach slices; let stand an hour.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on slices of bread and cut into desired shapes. Chill until ready to serve.

title: eileen's no flour cookies
directions: Mix together the sugar and peanut butter.
Mix together egg and vanilla.
Then mix with sugar and peanut butter.
Ball 1 teaspoon dough and then press with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender; drain.
Stir in beans, first 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
In another skillet, heat oil.
Quickly dip tortillas in hot oil just until softened.
Place 1/3 cup meat mixture on each tortilla.
Top each with chopped tomato; roll tightly.
Place, seam side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine; stir in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and enchilada sauce.
Cook and stir until boiling; boil 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican munch snack mix
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Melt margarine and drizzle over mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle taco seasoning mix evenly over mixture and mix well.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: cheesecake cream dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream until well blended. Refrigerate. Serve with assorted cut-up fruit, pound cake or cookies.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Set aside.
Combine other ingredients.
Add to dry mixture.
Stir until moist.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or glass baking loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown the sausage, peppers and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except macaroni and cheese. Cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in macaroni; cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes, until macaroni is tender.
Top individual servings with Mozzarella cheese.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple meat balls
directions: Mix and cook until thick. Pour over meatballs in casserole dish. Cover.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Pour in greased, 3-quart casserole.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Cook at 400° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix. Pour into large casserole. Sprinkle some of grated cheese on top. Bake about 45 minutes. Check occasionally to see that it is not burning on top. Sometimes I place a piece of foil over it toward the end of the cooking period.

title: the ultimate nanaimo bar recipe
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Add egg and stir to cook and thicken.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Press firmly into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; pour into pie shell and top with pie filling.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1 can of water. Place 1 pie crust in skillet and pour ingredients in and place other pie crust on top. Bake 45 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put chicken in pan with about 1/2 to 1 cup of water in bottom. Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour. When done, squeeze lemon all over.

title: easy  overnight breakfast
directions: Grease 9x13 dish.
Layer bread and other ingredients.
Pour egg and milk mixture over.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 30 mins. before baking.
Bake 350° for 35 mins.
Great with coffee cake and fresh fruit.

title: chicken macnuggets
directions: Wash and dry chicken breast.
Then cut into bite-size chunks. In a shallow bowl, mix flour, salt, and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
In small bowl, place milk and egg and beat together.
Dunk chicken nuggets in milk/egg mixture.
Then roll in breadcrumbs.
At this point, you can freeze the nuggets.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in pan.
Sprinkle in garlic salt to taste.
Drain grease from meat.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Put hamburger meat, cheese, taco sauce, water and chili in crock-pot.
Heat on high until hot.
Lower heat to keep warm. Serve with nacho chips or your favorite.
Would be great on a baked potato.

title: almond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square pan.

title: stuffed pepper casserole
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove ribs and seeds.
Chop edible portion of tops; set aside.
Wash peppers.
Place peppers in large kettle with 2-quarts salted water.
Bring to boiling; cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain peppers; set aside.
In hot margarine in medium skillet, saute chopped green pepper, onion and celery, 3 to 5 minutes, until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, basil, oregano, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Meanwhile, in large mixing bowl, combine remaining salt and pepper and Worcestershire.
Beat with spoon to blend.
Add chuck, rice and 1 cup of tomato mixture, mixing well.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Pour remaining tomato mixture over peppers.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes; mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour in buttered casserole dish with topping and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: california monkey bread
directions: Crumble yeast into a bowl and add milk or sprinkle dry yeast over milk.
Let stand until yeast is dissolved.
Meanwhile, beat dissolved yeast.
Add flour gradually and beat at least 10 minutes.
Cover bowl with damp cloth and let stand in warm place until doubled (2 hours).
Turn onto a floured board and knead for a minute.
Roll or pat out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Dip each piece in melted butter and place in layers in buttered 8 cup ring mold or buttered casserole.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
Bake at 400° until brown and then reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 50 minutes.
If top too brown, put sheet of foil on top.
Turn on platter.
Serve hot.

title: corn stuff
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Combine olive oil and garlic in 2-quart glass casserole. Microwave at High for 1 minute.
Add beans and onion; toss well. Cover with Saran Wrap, turning back edge to vent.
Microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes or until just tender.
Stir once.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Recover and microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes before serving.
Serve immediately or refrigerate covered with Saran Wrap and serve chilled.

title: barbecue dip
directions: Blend well.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: new orleans style spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix mushroom soup, chicken soup, tomato soup, and Velveeta (cut up) into ground beef.
Simmer low until cheese melts.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a bowl, beating until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and whipped topping.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix, alternating between the three layers.
Top with whipped topping.

title: german rice pudding
directions: Cook rice with water and salt for 1/2 hour or until done.
Add butter, salt and milk.
Pour into bowl; sprinkle with cinnamon. Cool in refrigerator.
A very rich and sweet dessert.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes.
Use tube or Bundt pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften margarine.
Add brown sugar and sugar.
Mix well.
Combine egg, vanilla and milk; beat smooth. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to above mixture.
Beat smooth again.
Add oats.
Add raisins, chocolate chips and/or nuts, if desired.
Mix well.
Drop cookies on well-greased cookie sheet and bake until light brown (10 to 12 minutes).

title: skier's french toast
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer until syrup like and pour in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice bread; place over syrup, layering as needed.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and cover.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In 6 to 8-quart kettle, heat butter.
Saute onions.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Boil and gradually add noodles and salt.
Cook uncovered 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 3 more minutes and add milk, cheese (cut in cubes) and pepper.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: baked scallops
directions: Parboil scallops for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and cut up. Cook onions and mushrooms in butter until brown.
Blend in flour and milk.
When thickened, add scallops and pour into casserole. Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Slice eggplant crosswise into 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Immerse in cold, well salted water for about 30 minutes.
(Brush each side with olive oil, place on a cookie sheet and broil on each side until golden brown, about 5 minutes per side.)
Set aside.

title: baked cranberries
directions: Mash and drain cranberries.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with sugar and lemon peel.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 35 minutes or until berries begin to burst.
Stir well to dissolve sugar.

title: kristy's perfectly peachy ice cream
directions: In a medium bowl, pour sugar over mashed peaches.
Add 1 cup milk and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the pudding mix and 3 cups of milk together. Add condensed milk and egg substitute. Fold in whipped topping, a little at a time, until it is mixed in thoroughly.
Combine peach mixture to pudding mixture and stir together.
Pour into freezer container and follow freezer directions.
Makes 4 quarts.
Leftover ice cream freezes great!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, then crumble in bottom of casserole dish. Add salt, chopped onion and soup.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Top with grated cheese and garlic salt.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fast-mix ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer can.
Freeze and ripen by basic directions if using a hand-crank ice cream churn or follow manufacturer's directions if using an electric freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.
No cooking of custard, this refreshing dessert tastes like ice milk.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and green peppers together.
Mix sugar, salt, celery seed and vinegar together and pour over sliced vegetables.
Ladle into jars, pouring liquid mixture over all. Place lids on jars and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Must be kept refrigerated.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and canning salt well and let set overnight.
Next morning, drain, rinse and drain well again.
In kettle mix remaining ingredients.
Cook altogether about 30 minutes.
Longer cooking will make thicker relish.

title: anita's chicken devan
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Layer chicken, broccoli and soup mixture in a medium casserole dish. Top with cheese, onions and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
Place flour on waxed paper and use to coat chicken pieces.

title: nut pineapple cheese spread
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients; mix until smooth and fluffy.
Spread on slice of favorite bread; top with another slice.
Can serve on favorite crackers.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and brown garlic (careful not to burn).
Add clam juice, salt and pepper; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add clams and cook for 10 more minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Serve over cooked linguini. Serves 4.

title: five minute no-bake pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade, milk and lemon juice and pour into graham cracker pie shell.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix well with large spoon until all flour is moistened. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator.

title: squash and potatoes
directions: Shred potatoes, squash and onions in frying pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour very little water over the vegetables and cook, covered, until almost tender.
Put a little oil or, if preferred, bacon grease and leave open while slightly browning.
All cooking should be done on medium heat.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: To the grated potatoes, add molasses, well beaten eggs, milk, shortening and orange peel.
Turn into an iron skillet and bake about 45 minutes.
At about the end of 25 minutes, sprinkle the brown sugar and cinnamon over the top.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine meat and Bisquick.
Mix with hands (easier if sausage is at room temperature).
Melt cheese over low heat.
Add sausage and Bisquick.
Roll in small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Flatten crescent rolls, pressing seams together to form a large rectangle.
Spread with butter and cover center with ham and cheese.
Roll up.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut each roll into fourths.
Makes 8.

title: secret pie
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl; beat well.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: peanut crunch toffee
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart saucepan melt butter or margarine over medium-high heat.
Immediately
begin
to
stir
in sugar with wooden spoon, also add syrup
and water at this time.
Cook to hard crack stage, candy
will
turn golden brown color.
Cover bottom of long baking dish	with half of nuts and white chocolate. Pour hot syrup
over
this;
put	remaining
nuts
and chocolate on top of hot candy.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
In saucepan put 2 cans soup.
When bubbly, put in tuna and seasoning.
Cook until seasoning is soft (may need to add a little milk).
In casserole dish, put a layer of noodles, layer of tuna mix, then a layer of cheese.
Continue layers until finished.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with bread crumbs and bake until golden brown.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients and mix well. Shape 12 meatballs.
In oven, brown meatballs in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: dover slop
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Place cubed potatoes in Dutch oven; cover with water. Boil until tender. Leaving potatoes and water in pot, add ground beef, diced onion or flakes, kidney beans, salt, Season-All and ketchup to taste (approximately 1 cup). Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; chop the other ingredients. Add it all together and mix.
Serve with crackers.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham cracker crust as directed on box for 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans, soup and 1/2 can of onions in a casserole dish and then add the other half on top.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt. Melt butter or margarine.
Add the 2 cups sugar and stir until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients slowly; beat well until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 66.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, old english, shredded cheese, cheddar cheese spread, worcestershire sauce and onion juice in bowl and let soften, mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup of cereal nuggets in bottom of 8-inch round cake pan. Combine remaining 1/4 cup cereal nuggets, ice cream, pudding mix and peanut butter in a large bowl; stir until mixture is well blended. Fold in whip topping. Spoon mixture into cake pan, spreading gently with a spatula. Cover and freeze 2 hours, until firm. Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well; dry thoroughly.
Put in oven and bake at 325° until you can pierce with a fork.
Cut the baked potatoes lengthwise and scoop out potato; whip with butter, cream, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Marinate chicken for 6 to 12 hours.
Tastes great.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 12 meat balls.
Brown on all sides in hot fat in skillet.
While meat browns, prepare Barbecue Sauce.
Place meat balls and sauce in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies(yield: 2 dozen cookies)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two baking sheets.

title: souperior meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large shallow baking pan, shape into loaf. Bake 1 hour or until done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Shake together vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in covered container until well mixed.
Add to all other combined ingredients and toss well.
Allow to marinate at room temperature for 1 hour. Add enough mayonnaise to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown meat and stir in tomato sauce.
Add salt and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add melted butter and eggs; mix lightly.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Do not beat.
Bake in pie shell (uncooked) at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm and golden brown.

title: mashed potato soup
directions: In a saucepan, saute the onion in butter until tender. Add milk, potatoes and seasonings. Heat through. Makes 2 servings.

title: tender pot roast
directions: You will also need 1 oven cooking bag.

title: french onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter. Add broth, water and sauce.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Put in ovenproof container.
Add French bread with cheese over top until melted.

title: minestra ai funghi(mushroom soup)
directions: Clean the mushrooms with a cloth to rid them of dirt, but do not wash them.
Cut into julienne strips.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef, onion and taco sauce.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl right before serving and add to beef mix.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in center of sheet of aluminum foil about 2 1/2-inches long and 1 1/2-inches wide. Combine remaining ingredients; spread on meat.
Seal foil securely.
Place in baking pan.
Bake 3 1/2 hours or until tender. Spoon gravy over roast before serving.

title: ann's soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with bay leaf and garlic in chicken broth.
Mash potatoes in broth as it cooks.
Add other ingredients with cheese and milk last.
(Do not boil milk.)

title: glazed pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Add sifted flour and baking powder; alternate with milk.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: puddin' fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add fruit and chill.
Good potluck dish.

title: baked popcorn
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Add brown sugar, syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil 5 more minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla mixture.
(Mix soda and vanilla before adding to pan.)
Mix. Sauce will foam up.
Pour over popped corn and mix very well until corn is covered.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, mixing every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and keep mixing until it cools.
I use large aluminum (turkey pan) for corn and wooden spoon and fork sprayed with Pam to keep it from sticking.
Also cleans up better.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine lettuce, celery, onions, shredded carrots, green pepper and tiny peas in their frozen state.
Spread over top:
1 cup of mayonnaise mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Shred any kind of cheese over top of that.
Top with bacon and sliced hard-boiled eggs, if desired.
Can be made 24 hours ahead.

title: chicken soup
directions: Clean chicken and remove visible fat.
Be sure to remove pouch from the inside of the chest cavity that contains liver, neck, etc.
Put chicken in soup pot.
Fill pot with enough water to almost cover chicken. Add onion, cleaned carrots, celery, salt, pepper and dill.
You can clean dill and tie it with a string to hold bunch together.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour or until drumstick is soft (fork will enter easily). Remove vegetables and set aside.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Blend chicken, carrots and celery in a blender until totally smooth. Put chicken mixture back into broth.
Cut up onion and put into broth.
To serve with noodles, put 2 ladles of soup per person in a pot. Add a handful of thin egg noodles per person.
Heat until noodles are done.
Freezes well.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line a greased 9-inch pie pan with one crust.
Set aside.

In boiling water, boil the potatoes, carrots and onion for 2 minutes; drain. Combine all vegetables and turkey with soup and milk. Pour filling into pie pan. Top with second crust. Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top of crust to vent and bake for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Allow to settle for about 15 minutes before cutting.

title: pecan puffs
directions: In bowl, beat egg whites and salt until peaks form, about 5 to 8 minutes. Fold in vanilla, pecans and brown sugar. Drop by well rounded teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 200° for 50 to 55 minutes or until firm to the touch. Store in airtight container. Makes 3 dozen.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and microwave 4 minutes on High. Remove and stir.
Microwave 4 more minutes.
Remove.
Stir in butter; microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour immediately onto a lightly greased cookie sheet (tilt cookie sheet so mixture runs in each direction).
Do not use any utensils; let cool.

title: macaroni & cheese
directions: Boil macaroni then drain.
In a 8x8 dish, add macaroni, cheese, butter and cream.
Mix together and place sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: In pan melt butter.
Add cocoa, flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda onto wax paper.
Line and grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with wax paper.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in banana.
Stir in flour mixture, fold in wheat germ, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Loosen around edges with a knife, turn out onto a wire rack.
Peel off wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion and salt.
Mix well. Shape into 15 meatballs, 1 1/2-inches in size.
Arrange in microwave-safe pie plate.

title: italian sausage casserole
directions: Brown Little Zizzlers with garlic and onion.
Boil noodles until done.
Mix noodles with Little Zizzlers sausage, spaghetti sauce and half of cheese.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: venison jerky
directions: Marinate venison in glass container for 8 to 12 hours.
Drain and place in 150° oven for 12 hours.
You can lay meat on a cookie sheet, but drain off liquid as needed.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Boil chicken legs until tender; take meat off bones and cut in small pieces.
Cook onions until clear in small amount of fat or in the microwave.
Mix all ingredients, except tortillas and cheese, to make creamy sauce.
Use a large casserole dish; spray with Pam.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese until all is used; make at least three layers of each.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Add about 1/2 cup of extra broth to top.
Use broth from chicken legs.
Cover and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 12 to 15 servings.
Make several bowls at a time.
Freezes well.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll on floured cloth and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
May be be ahead and allowed to rise or not.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix ingredients all together.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar, eggs and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add orange extract. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch chips. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Cook at 375° for 10 minutes (do not overcook).

title: braised celery and peas
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine vegetables, butter, water and salt.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 minutes.
Stir and add peas. Cover; microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Cool.
Drain pineapple and set juice aside.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows to first mixture.
Let jell.
Cook sugar, flour, pineapple juice and egg until thick.
Stir in Dream Whip.
Spread on top of salad.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and milk.
Pour on top.
Keep in refrigerator.
Grate cheese on top.

title: dilly bread
directions: Heat to lukewarm the buttermilk or cottage cheese. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 c. warm water;

add to buttermilk. Add all other ingredients but flour. Beat briskly for several minutes (may use mixer). Add flour and beat briskly with spoon for several minutes. Put in 2 qt. baking bowl or loaf bread pan. Let rise 30-40 min. or until doubled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs and little cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: strawberry cool and fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice and stir constantly until slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in Cool Whip until smooth.
Chill if necessary.
Mixture should mound as you spoon into pie crust.
Use fresh strawberries to garnish.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rice chex dessert
directions: Melt oleo; add nuts and toast until brown.
Add brown sugar, coconut and Rice Chex to first mixture.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Cover with 1/2 gallon of softened ice cream (vanilla).
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Press down. Freeze.

title: lemon muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add well-beaten egg yolks and beat until light.
Add the lemon juice alternately with the flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt, mixing thoroughly after each addition (do not overmix).
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and grated lemon peel.
Fill buttered muffin pans 3/4 full and bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: breezy brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until very light.
Add eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Blend in chocolate and flour.
Pour into greased 10 1/2 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. During last 5 minutes of baking, prepare frosting.

title: chicken elegantlincoln, nebraska
directions: Between two sheets of wax paper, pound chicken breasts one half inch thickness.

title: homemade oreos
directions: Mix and roll into ball size of quarters (spreads when cooking). Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 minutes. Cookies look almost underdone; cracks on top when done. Let sit on pan a few minutes.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in Pyrex baking pan. Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Place one can of fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Place in 350° oven and bake.
Batter will rise to top and form crust.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato.
Cut off 1/4 and put in bowl.
Start adding powdered sugar to 1/4 boiled potato until dough forms.
Roll out with rolling pin until flat like a tortilla.
Put peanut butter on it like a jelly sandwich and roll up (log form).
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Remove from refrigerator and cut in slices.
Excellent candy for Christmas.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix cocoa, coffee and boiling water.
Cover and heat.
Serve in demitasse cups.
Top with whipped cream and a sprinkle of nutmeg.

title: bannockwaterford, michigan
directions: These Italian hard cookies are great with coffee or cappucino and are trendy, too!
Wrap the mix bag in red, white and green tissue papers twisted together to make a big pompom.
Include a bottle of anise extract in the gift basket.
You can make a large batch for yourself; they keep for a long time.

title: allyssa's lasagna
directions: Add tomato sauce, sweet basil, oregano, salt, dry mustard, thyme, cayenne pepper and paprika to ground beef.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
Break the lasagna noodles in half; cook in boiling salt water until done.
Leave in water until used.
Arrange meat mixture, noodles and cheese in layers in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cheese sandwiches
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put 6 slices of bread in bottom.
Put cheese slices on top of bread and cover with remaining bread slices.
Beat milk, eggs and salt well.
Pour over sandwiches and let stand 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes or until sandwiches are browned.
Serve immediately.

title: saucepan coconut chocolate bars
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugars and water. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Add coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour in greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: In medium bowl, cut cream cheese and butter into biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk.
Turn onto lightly floured surface; knead 8 to 10 times.
On wax paper, roll dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Invert onto greased baking sheet; remove paper. Spread preserves down center of dough.
Make 2 1/2-inch long cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides.
Fold strips over filling.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and frost.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: savory steak slices
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut to 5 inches wide.
Mix soy sauce and some white wine.
Marinate meat for 24 hours; turn occasionally. Oil steaks on both sides.
Place in broiler pan without rack. Broil meat 6 inches from heat for 1 minute on each side.
Turn steak; broil 5 minutes longer.
Turn and broil 5 more minutes, or until medium rare.
Let cool.
Brush meat with pan juices.
Chill, lightly covered, until serving time.
To serve, slice thin. Arrange on platter with watercress and radishes with bread nearby. Use prime or choice grade of beef.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and cheese. Add sugar, salt, vanilla, eggs and flour.
Bake at 300° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Add red food coloring and cocoa.
Blend well. Mix together salt, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add to the sugar mixture alternately with flour.
Mix together soda and vinegar. Fold into batter with as little mixing as necessary to distribute evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: burrito crescent squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef with onion and seasoning mix; drain.
Stir in refried beans.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together; add unbeaten eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda and spices.
Combine applesauce and preserves.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place all vegetables in large Tupperware container.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over veggies.
Refrigerate several hours, tossing occasionally.
Before serving, remove garlic and bay leaf and drain veggies.

title: zucchini and green peppers
directions: In large skillet, saute bacon until crisp; remove bacon bits and set aside.
In hot drippings, saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add pepper strips and zucchini; sprinkle with salt and thyme.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes, or just until vegetables are tender.
Turn into serving dish; sprinkle with bacon bits.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese puff sandwich
directions: Cut crusts off bread; butter on one side.
Place 1 slice of bread in well-greased oblong Pyrex dish.
Top with slice of cheese, then ham, chicken or turkey.
Put on remaining slice of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over sandwiches.
Mix flakes in butter; sprinkle on top.
Soak overnight or for about 8 to 10 hours.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt ora miles cake recipe
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, then add flour a little at a time, until mixed.
Add vanilla. Bake in 3 to 4 (8-inch) layer pans, depending on how thick you want the cake to be.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: mandarin jello
directions: Dilute Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in mandarin oranges, frozen orange juice and crushed pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm and spread with topping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature.
Mix well.
Add chopped scallions (save tops), garlic and salt.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecans and scallion tops.

title: baked fish in cheese sauce
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Cook until bubbly, add salt, mustard, dill weed and cayenne.
Remove from heat, stir in half and half gradually.
Return to heat and cook until thick. Stir in 1 cup cheese, mix in mussels.
Pour cheese sauce over fish, top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoon of dough into powdered sugar. Roll in sugar and shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Brine:
3/4 cup salt, NOT iodized, to 1 gallon water.

title: harvest applesauce
directions: Combine apples, water and (if desired) cinnamon in an 8 to 10-inch quart kettle.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
Remove cinnamon. Press apples through a food mill or sieve.
Return pulp to kettle. Stir in sugar.
If necessary, add 1/2 to 1 cup water for desired consistency.
Bring to boil.
Makes 6 pints.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut into pieces.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Enough mayonnaise or salad dressing should be used to mix to make spreading easy.
Also good with Ritz crackers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind the apples, oranges and sugar together; let set overnight.
Add the jello, hot water and chopped pecans.
Mix well and let set.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Place sliced corned beef on rye bread. Top with kraut that has been cooked with 1 teaspoon bacon fryings for 10 minutes. Cover with sliced Swiss cheese, then another slice bread. Butter both slices on outside. Brown each side in a skillet or on griddle until toasty brown.

title: cabbage and corned beef
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Boil until tender.
Put corned beef into cabbage.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: lisa's veggie dip
directions: Cream together and refrigerate.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix pickles with juice, onion and pepper in the blender until chopped.
Drain and then add mayonnaise.

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Wash zucchini, slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Parboil 3 minutes in small amount of salted water.
Drain and set aside.
Brown meat slightly, add onion and cook until onion is opaque.
Add salt, pepper and oregano, mixing well.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan, blend in flour and simmer, stirring for 1 minute.
Add milk and cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil and has thickened.
Stir in cheese.
In 2-quart buttered casserole, arrange mixture of zucchini and meat mixture.
Spoon on half of cheese sauce.
Repeat layers ending with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serve immediately.

title: almond thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Add butter; blend with a wooden spoon until a soft dough forms.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with thumb.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
While still warm, put icing in middle.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed by hand.
Pour in ungreased 11 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, rice, onion, celery and water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup over ingredients; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "liz's beef burgundy"
directions: Cut round steak into bite size cubes; shake with flour to coat evenly, being sure all the flour is used.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet.
Brown part of the steak cubes on all sides, set aside and repeat with remaining pieces.

title: rum or whiskey balls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients; mix well.
Roll into bite-size balls.

title: brownies to perfection
directions: Prepare your favorite homemade or mix brownies.
Cook as directed except take out 5 minutes before done.
Top with thin mints and put back in oven for last 5 minutes.
Take brownies out and spread the melted mints over the brownies.

title: apples and cream cheese dip
directions: Chop peanuts into small pieces.
Add cream cheese, milk and brown sugar.
Serve with apple slices.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cocoa, butter and milk in pan over low heat. Stir regularly. Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix together. Dip onto wax paper. Let cool. Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add all of mixture to squash and cook in a double boiler 1 hour, then put in casserole and bake 30 minutes in oven.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, if desired.

title: goop cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread to corners.
Blend 2 eggs, 1 box powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Pour on top of cake mixture. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into small squares when cooled.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour corn in casserole dish.
Break eggs in bowl.
Whisk and add milk.
Break crackers in small pieces, not crumbs.
Mix all; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: In medium saucepan melt chocolate, butter and margarine over low heat.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Stir in sugar, then beat in eggs.
Blend in flour, mixing well.
Mix in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan on rack.
Cut into squares.

title: ham 'n cheese pinwheels
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth. Stir in horseradish and chives.
Spread each meat slice with about 1 tablespoon cheese mixture.
Top with cheese slice and spread with another tablespoon cheese mixture.
Roll up.
Chill.
Before serving, slice each roll into five pieces. Serve with toothpicks, if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked beans casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour in 9 x 11-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Served with a smile makes everyone happy.

title: porcupines
directions: Blend peanut butter, milk and sugar with wooden spoon, then knead with your hands.
Divide into balls and roll in chopped peanuts.

title: three-in-one meat loaf
directions: Grind veal, pork and round.
Then, mix all ingredients together by hand.
Put in loaf pan.
Place bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: turkish lamb stew
directions: Toss lamb with flour.
Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet. Add lamb and cook over medium-high heat, turning to brown about 3 minutes.
Remove lamb and set aside.
Add onion, red pepper and garlic to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, about 3 minutes.
Add lamb and next 3 ingredients.
Drain tomatoes and measure 1/4 cup juice; pour into skillet.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients to skillet.
Stir well; bring to boil. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: hershey's kiss peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately after taking out of oven with chocolate kiss or chocolate star.
Place on greased cookie sheet.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix milk, sugar, cocoa in saucepan. Cook until boils, then turn on low heat cook 15 minutes stirring often.
When done add butter and vanilla.
Heat until smooth, put on cake or ice cream or on pudding.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Press with cookie press or flat bottomed glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar generously on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Take 2 cups of water and juice from pineapple; bring to a boil. Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add the other ingredients and fold in. Save enough whipped cream to spread over top, then sprinkle a few nuts over top.
Put into baking dish or pan and chill.
Cut into squares or put in custard cup; top with a teaspoon of whipped cream and nuts.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: fried okra patties
directions: Mix all together and spoon drop in hot oil in a frying pan. Brown each side until golden brown.

title: barbecue ham
directions: Score steaks in diamond shape.

title: homemade pizza(2 pizzas)
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water in large mixing bowl; stir until dissolved.
Add shortening, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually add remaining flour, mixing with hands until dough is stiff enough to leave side of bowl.
Turn out dough onto lightly floured board.
Cover with bowl; let rest 10 minutes. Knead 8 to 10 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.

Place in lightly greased medium bowl; turn dough to bring up greased side. Cover with towel; let rise in warm place, free from drafts, until double in bulk, about 1 hour, or until 2 fingers poked into dough leave indentations.
Punch down dough with fist; turn out onto lightly floured surface.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
In a medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Fold in squash and onion.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Mix all together; chill at least 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with cutter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
