Bake 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Combine fruits and marshmallows in large bowl. Beat eggs until light; gradually add sugar, light cream and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over fruit mixture lightly.
Chill 24 hours.

title: rhubarb custard pie(yield:  two 9-inch pies)
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces (1-inch).
Cream together sugar and beaten eggs; add flour, then vanilla and lastly butter.
Blend until smooth.
Add rhubarb, then pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° until center of pie no longer shimmies when shook (don't overbake).
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: icebox cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk over low heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Mix other ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add melted mixture to this and mix very well.
Pack firmly into a long pan or glass dish and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Stir in pineapple juice (4 cups). Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir in jello. Whip milk until it forms peaks. Mix milk and jello mixture. Layer pie plates with vanilla wafers. Pour filling into pans. Leave in the refrigerator overnight. Makes 3 pies.

title: sunkist lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 egg, butter and cake mix (dry) until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat the remaining mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Beat 2 eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice with mixer until fluffy and foamy.
Pour over hot crust; spread with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake about 15 minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Cool, cut into bars.
Yields 32 bars.

title: pineapple plantation punch
directions: Combine 1 can pineapple juice and peppermint.
Pour into 2 ice cube trays.
Freeze until firm.
Combine remaining juice concentrate and 1 quart ice water in large pitcher.
Stir in soda. Pour over pineapple ice cubes in punch bowl.
Yields 30 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix soup, water or wine and flour until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Take first 3 ingredients.
Mix and let sit for 30 minutes.
Mix the sugar and eggs into the oat mixture.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry parfaits
directions: Can use blueberries, strawberries or peaches.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crush chips in bottom of greased baking dish.
Brown ground beef; drain and spoon into dish.
Chop up onion over beef and half of grated cheese.
Add the two soups, Ro-Tel and water.
Take spatula and run through to mix.
Grate rest of cheese on top and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and applesauce together.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to applesauce mixture.
Add raisins; mix again.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. When cool, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: pretty pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Cut or slice broccoli and cauliflower.
Chop onion, tomato and cucumber.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl, except Italian dressing mix. Mix dressing mix with vinegar and oil according to package.
Toss to coat well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: avocado dip salad
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients and spread onto a serving plate or platter.
Layer next 5 ingredients on top of avocado spread in the order given.
Sprinkle alfalfa sprouts over all.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: taco pie
directions: Layer each item on a plate or dish and use the chips to dip with.

title: "twice baked" potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes as usual.
Add cream cheese, dip and garlic salt. Put in casserole.
Brush top with butter; sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: basil and broccoli chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in margarine; cook until tender.
Remove chicken.
Add rice to drippings; saute until rice is golden brown.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups of water, contents of seasoning packet and basil.
Place chicken over rice mixture; bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Top with broccoli and tomatoes.
Cover; continue to simmer 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is well cooked.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour nuts and coconut into pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until lightly browned.
Arrange apples on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks. Drizzle on apples.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and brown; drain well.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and spread in buttered Pyrex dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning; beat well. Pour over cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: joelene's quick snack
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together in bowl.
Using spoons, place on	ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.	Bake until golden brown, about 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: james' hush puppies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and fry in deep fat.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix with other ingredients; let set overnight.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic or enamel container.
Soak turkey for 24 hours.
Dry off and bake as usual.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and lemon juice.
Toss gently to mix.
Spoon into crust and dot with margarine.
Top with second crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.

Brush with milk and sprinkle with 2 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Cover edge of crust with strips of aluminum foil after the first 20 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread on slice of ham.
Roll up.
Chill overnight before cutting, then slice 1-inch long.

title: great-grannie birk christmas cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix slow.
Add mixed fruit, nuts and juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into mixture.
Garnish with cherries and pineapple before baking.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 450° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: deluxe mash potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; mash and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add rest of ingredients, except paprika.
Beat until smooth.
Add to potatoes and beat well.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reheat time, 15 minutes.
(Can be frozen.)

title: old fashion peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and milk in small saucepan. Boil to 232° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla flavoring. Stir until thick and pour into buttered pan. Let cool.

title: green chili and cream cheese dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir until sugar dissolves (2 to 3 minutes).
Stir in chilies.
Put in a small bowl, cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Drain, pressing mixture with a spoon to remove moisture.
Stir in cream cheese.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: tim's favorite tuna cakes
directions: Drain tuna; mix with eggs.
Crumble crackers.
Mix together; add salt and pepper.
Make out into patties.
In skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Fry patties until golden brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Process until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: orange butter crescent rolls
directions: In bowl, soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water tested to 110° to 115°.
Stir in eggs, 1/4 cup of the sugar, the sour cream, 6 tablespoons butter or margarine and salt.
Stir in 2 3/4 cups flour.
On floured surface, knead in enough flour to make a moderately soft dough that is smooth and elastic (3 to 5 minutes). Place in greased bowl; turn over once.
Let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Turn out onto floured surface; divide in two and shape in balls.
Cover; let rest ten minutes.
Roll each ball into a 12-inch circle.
Brush each with 1 tablespoon of the remaining butter (melted).	Combine remaining sugar, 3/4 cup coconut and the orange peel; sprinkle over circles.
Cut each circle into 12 pie-like wedges.
Start at wide end and roll each triangle or wedge.	Arrange rolls, pinwheel fashion, in two greased 9-inch round pans or cookie sheets.
Cover; let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Immediately remove from pans; place on wire racks over waxed paper.
Top with glaze and remaining 1/4 cup coconut.
Makes 2 pans of 12 rolls.

title: hardy ham and cabbage chowder
directions: In soup pot, saute celery, onion and garlic over medium heat. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about one hour.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange 6 slices French bread in bottom of pan.
In blender, blend eggs with cottage cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, cinnamon and poppy seed on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with warm syrup and powdered sugar (optional).

title: cold sesame noodles *
directions: In blender, blend first ten ingredients, reserving 1/2 tablespoon sesame oil.
In kettle of boiling, salted water, cook noodles until al dente; drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain again well and toss in bowl with remaining sesame oil.
Mound noodles on platter; drizzle with sesame mixture and sprinkle with scallions.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Serves four as main course.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, salt and 3/4 cup half and half in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Do not boil.

title: kathy's rum cake
directions: Cake:
Follow mix directions, except substitute 1/2 cup water with 1/2 cup rum.
Prepare 2 pans by melting 2 tablespoons of margarine in each, then sprinkle lightly with finely chopped pecans.
Pour half of batter in each pan and baking according to package.
Cool cakes and prepare filling.

title: super slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and pepper.
Chop olives and pour sugar over all.
In a saucepan, mix mustard, celery seed, salt, pepper, vinegar and salad oil.
Boil for 3 minutes and pour over vegetables and toss.
Store covered in refrigerator for 12 hours. This will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion and seasonings in a saucepan, mixing well. Gradually add water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour half the soup mixture into a 3 quart casserole.
Then
making two layers of each, add the rice (right from the box) and the chicken.
Top with remaining soup mixture. Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir well after 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Makes 8 servings.

title: busy day cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into bowl.
Put everything else in and blend.
Then beat about 3 minutes.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Let potatoes cool.
Add egg and flour.
Mix well.
Form in balls, add to boiling water (salted).
Cook for 10 minutes and remove from water.
Cut bacon in small pieces, dice onion and fry until crisp.
Do not drain.
Serve over dumplings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender and drain. Add butter and egg.
Mix salt and dry mustard with 1 tablespoon of hot water and add to milk (but do not add to macaroni yet).
Toss macaroni with grated cheese, leaving enough to sprinkle some on top.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Pour in milk mixture and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and pour into a glass baking dish.
Bake at 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked (about 5 minutes). Transfer to food processor or blender; chop finely.
Beat eggs well in large bowl.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Stir in the cheese, onion and broccoli.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spoon into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Bake until set, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before cutting.

title: bread pudding
directions: Lightly grease casserole.
Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar. Slowly add milk and vanilla.
Pour into casserole dish.
Butter both sides of bread and break into pieces.
Place on top of mixture in casserole and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a shallow pan of water.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening to water and bring to a boil. Add flour all at once and stir until ball forms in center of pan.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Shape on oiled cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes in hot oven at 450°.
Reduce temperature to moderate 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until done. Fill with cream filling, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; leave overnight.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fill 3 well-greased coffee cans half full.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions. Mix salad dressing, vinegar, salt and sugar together and pour over the cucumbers and onions. Don't stir until ready to serve. Last at least a week in refrigerator.

title: fruit crumble
directions: Mix until crumbly flour, sugar, oatmeal and melted butter. Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Press firm.
Next, spread can of fruit pie filling.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with ice cream, if desired.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water and lemon juice.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange and pecans.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Boil last 4 ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Marinate overnight.
Pack in small containers and freeze. Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks or more.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat the oil, sugar and eggs together.
Mix together the carrots, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Bake 20 minutes on a cookie sheet at 350°.

title: jiffy turkey paella
directions: In a large saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato juice, oil, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Stir in rice.
Bring to boiling.
Add artichoke hearts, turkey and olives.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven 1 hour and 25 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring once or twice.
If desired, garnish with stuffed green olives.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in a slightly greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn cake onto platter.
Slice.
Store any leftovers in a sealed container.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix together and top with dry bread crumbs.
Bake at moderate oven heat until done, about 45 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients in processor or blender.
Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese and blend until combined.
Season to taste with salt.
Place lettuce in a large bowl.
Add enough dressing to season to taste.
Toss well.
Divide salad among plates.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.

title: italian easter ricotta pie
directions: Cream sugar and Ricotta, add flour, eggs and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti for 100
directions: Cook meat until beginning to turn color.
Add onion and continue to cook until just done and light brown.
Drain off fat. Put in large container or divide into 2 pots.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the spaghetti.
Simmer about 2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Sprinkle lightly with flour.
Add hot water and bouillon cubes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Toast French bread and cut into pieces.
Place toasted bread on bottom of bowl; fill bowl with soup.
Put a handful of grated cheese on top of soup. Place bowls of soup under broiler until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets in this solution until hot and pack in jars and seal.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together bread and pineapple chunks and place in a greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread/pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Casserole can be refrigerated before baking. Great with ham.

title: dressed-up chicken breast
directions: Combine croutons, sage, onion, egg and bouillon.
Place about 3 tablespoons stuffing in center of each chicken breast. Place 2 slices
dried
beef on top of each mound of dressing. Roll	up each breast tightly and serve with toothpicks.
Cook bacon briefly on
both
sides
until partly done but a little soft.
Wrap
2 slices
bacon around each chicken roll.
Place rolls in a greased baking dish.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Get Bisquick 'n milk 'n eggs in and fry them.
Put on plate and eat 'em.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into long pan.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Pour over cooled crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add tea bags and remove from heat. Cover and let stand 3 minutes and remove tea bags.
Combine tea with all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add ginger ale to cold punch and serve at once.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Combine margarine and graham cracker crumbs and put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk on crust.
Layer chocolate morsels, coconut; press down with hands and put on walnuts.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until lightly brown at 325°.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, milk, eggs, vanilla and sugar and pour into blender and blend.
Pour into a dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain, mash and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in oleo.
Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs and cheese in a baking dish.
Mix well.
Cover casserole with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and brown.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Heavily butter and sugar Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until deep golden color.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate vegetables overnight in 1/3 bottle of dressing. Add another 1/3 bottle to cooked rotini. Mix together. Add parmesan cheese and last 1/3 of bottle just before serving.

title: roll out cookies
directions: In large bowl of mixer, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Stir into creamed mixture with a spoon.
Roll out and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well with a fork.
Pour into nice serving dish; cool.
Best if made the night before.

title: burnt cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edge of pan. Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick (3 minutes). Gradually beat cream into egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and pour into 6 (6 oz.) cups. Place cups into baking pan that has 1/2 inch water in the bottom. Bake until set, 45 minutes. Remove cups and chill. Sprinkle with sugar and place under broiler and cook until topping is medium brown. Chill and Serve.

title: goat cheese with sun-dried tomatoes and rosemary
directions: Cover dried tomato halves with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain and chop.
Combine tomatoes and next 3 ingredients. Cover and chill up to 4 hours.
Slice the baguette thinly.
Brush rounds with additional olive oil.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Just before serving, place goat cheese on a plate and top with marinated tomatoes.
Serve with baguette rounds and garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs, if desired.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time: 6:00.

title: native seasoning(also called creole seasoning or pound salt)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in a jar for future use.
Hot red pepper is often used instead of black for fish seasoning. This seasoning is used for flavoring all types of meat, fish, chicken, turkey and duck.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut with sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
(Sauerkraut may turn darker color.)
Add remaining vegetables.
Mix vinegar and oil.
Stir into vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Chill.

title: chicken, broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken parts.
Boil noodles and boil broccoli.
Mix the can of golden mushroom soup with cream of chicken and broccoli soup.
Debone chicken and mix all ingredients, except cheese, together in a casserole dish.
After all ingredients are mixed, add shredded cheese on top.
Put in oven until cheese has melted, then take out and serve.

title: company swiss steak
directions: Cut steak in pieces.
Pound salt and flour in each side. Brown in oil; cook onion until limp.
Add all other ingredients except mushrooms.
Simmer 1 hour covered.
Add mushrooms.
Cook additional 30 minutes.
Should be watched; may need more liquid. Add wine or water.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch round pans. Cream the oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time; add dry ingredients; stir in carrots and nuts. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: nutty cheese cookies
directions: Mix cheese, flour, oil, salt and cayenne until crumbly.
Add milk and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on oiled cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt, pepper and onions to taste.
Cook noodles 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place in bottom of a baking dish. Add hamburger mixture and remaining ingredients.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Combine lemon juice and Kikkoman.
Add steak and marinate in covered dish in refrigerator overnight.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Heat cranberry juice and pour over gelatin and cool.
Press other ingredients into the bottom of the mold and pour gelatin mixture over it.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Measure flour by sifting.
Blend all ingredients (dry).
Stir into shortening mixture.
Chill dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten crisscross style with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach on a beach punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve over crushed ice.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add unbeaten egg whites and 1 cup of the defrosted frozen strawberries.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan (greased and floured) for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cajun corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Generously grease 2 cornbread pans or muffin cups.
If using cast-iron pans, place greased pans in hot oven 20 minutes while preparing batter.
For a crispy outside crust, batter should sizzle and hiss when spooned into pans.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli, drain well. Stir in soup and sour cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly coat 6-cup bundt pan or tube pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in large casserole dish.	Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes, until it bubbles.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: To boiling water, add Jell-O, tapioca pudding and vanilla pudding.
Let this mixture thicken and add remaining ingredients. Serve when chilled.

title: yogurt pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix yogurt and then add Cool Whip. Pour mixture into pie crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 20 minutes before serving to make cutting easier.

title: pan-scalloped broccoli and cauliflower
directions: Bring 1/2 inch of water to boil in a large pot or Dutch oven. Add cauliflower and broccoflower florets.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 6 to 9 minutes, until firm-tender when
pierced. Drain, rinse with cold water, and drain again.
Repeat with broccoli florets, but cook only 3-5 minutes, until crisp-tender. Refrigerate tightly covered.

title: corn cakes
directions: *If using all-purpose cornmeal, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking soda.

title: country sausage apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium skillet, brown sausage. Drain well.
Stir in celery, onion, marjoram, walnuts, apples and cheese; pour into one pie crust.
Cut a large apple shape from remaining pie crust and place on top of filling.
Cover top of pie with aluminum foil and bake 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frosting
directions: Melt margarine in a pot.
Add flour, then add the milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Set aside to cool.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grits souffle
directions: Slice cheese. Mix margarine and cheese with cooked grits. Beat eggs in measuring cup; finish filling cup with milk.
Mix with grits, butter and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven in covered casserole dish until a little brown and mixture thickens.

title: diabetic fruitcake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well and bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven in greased and floured loaf pan.
After cake has baked for 1 hour, cover with foil to prevent cake from drying out during rest of baking.

title: potato soup
directions: Wash and peel potatoes; chop or dice.
Peel onion.
Cook in small amount of water until tender.
Add milk, cheese soup, salt and pepper.
Bring to a slow boil.
Serve.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
If batter is too dry, add 2 tablespoons milk.
Roll in balls and then in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and push chocolate star in center of cookies. Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: grandma lila's ginger cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add egg and mix well, then add molasses.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and mix well. Roll out thin on lightly floured board.
Cut out desired shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: flopper pudding
directions: Spread half of Vanilla Wafer crumbs on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1-1/2 inch baking pan.
Cream butter, gradually add confectioners sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat 1 minute more.
Beat egg whites until stiff then fold into yolk mixture.
(Mixture may look curdled.)
Beat at medium speed for a few seconds or until smooth. Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Carefully spread mixture over crumbs. Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm, 5 hours or overnight. Cut into 10 squares.
Garnish with cherries.

title: mustard
directions: Heat vinegar.
Mix all other ingredients, except butter.
Add to vinegar and stir until bubbles.
Cook 1 minute, stirring. Remove from heat, stir in butter or margarine.

title: layered hamburger bake
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt, pepper and cooked noodles.
Set aside. Stir together cream cheese, sour cream, milk and onion.
In 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of the ground beef mixture, 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture and all of the spinach.
Top with remaining ground beef mixture.
Cover and bake 40 minutes or until bubbly in 350° oven.
Uncover and spread remaining cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hot licks(barbecue sauce)
directions: Great on ribs, grilled shrimp, hamburgers and even baked beans (add while cooking).

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add sugar, water, vanilla and cocoa and mix well.
Add uncooked oatmeal and mix well.
Chill mixture for 2 hours and roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole(requested for every family gathering)
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender, about 8 minutes. Mix together soup, onion, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Combine mixture with drained/cooked broccoli and stir well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine and combine with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture over broccoli and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 12.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Blend in oil with fork.
Add water and mix well.
If too dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons more of oil.
Roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: 3 coconut pies
directions: Cook all except egg whites until thick; beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold 1/2 into cooled mixture.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar to remaining egg whites and top pies.
Brown under broiler.

title: creole steak
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add meat and brown evenly on both sides. Remove meat from skillet and drain well on paper towels.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter.
Shape into small balls.
Press a stuffed olive into each ball.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. These will freeze well.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Mix in flour; add nuts and chocolate chips. Put in 9 x 13 baking pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Arrange rolls in greased, fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Cook butter and remaining ingredients over low heat until mixture bubbles; pour over rolls.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks. Beat egg yolks. Add all ingredients except egg whites.
Blend and stir. Fold beaten egg whites into cake batter.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: billig broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli and break in chunks.
Saute onion in oleo until soft.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Place in casserole dish and bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered 15 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a 300° oven to cook down.
The sauce should be very thick and smooth.
The longer you can bake it, the smoother the taste.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, milks and Cool Whip; mix well in a large bowl.
Set aside in refrigerator.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in a flat deep dish.
Pour pudding mixture over this; alternate layers, ending with vanilla wafers on top.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Slice carrots diagonally into 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick chunks. Cook 7 to 10 minutes.
Combine in small saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes.
Add orange juice and boil 1 minute.
Add butter.
Pour over hot carrots and toss.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: herbed dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender or food processor. Whirl until the mixture is smooth.
Place in a jar with a tight-fitting lid.
Refrigerate for up to 2 weeks.
Shake well before using.

title: main dish pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta without salt.
Combine ingredients, tossing well.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with tomato wedges.

title: corned beef dill dip
directions: Slice corned beef into small strips.
Mix all dip ingredients. Cut center out of the bread.
Break bread into small pieces for dipping.
Put dip into the hole in bread loaf.
Bread should be shaped like a bowl.
Arrange on plate with bread bowl in center and pieces around the edge.

title: ice cream cake
directions: This recipe, like a sonata, is performed in three parts. First, line the bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Split them in half, so that you are using only the single cake.
Mix vanilla ice cream with orange juice.
Pour this into mold over the bottom layer of ladyfingers.
If ice cream becomes too soft, re-freeze slightly before pouring.
Freeze firm.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Measure cereal into large bowl.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt 5 cups of marshmallows, corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Mix until completely coated with chocolate.
Stir in 1 cup marshmallows.
Press mixture in pan with buttered back of spoon. Let stand for at least 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Boil noodles, rinse and drain.
Mix into boiled noodles the remaining ingredients, except the potato chips.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove and put crushed potato chips on top and bake for 15 more minutes. Very good.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and pour over brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut when lukewarm. Eat as many as you want, but watch for enlarged waists!

title: nitey nite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on foil-covered cookie sheet.
Place in oven, close door and turn oven off.
Do not open until morning.
Remove from foil and store.

title: orange cool whip salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese and mix.
Add fruit; mix. Add Cool Whip; mix.
Chill.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Beat together all ingredients except crab.
Add crab and pour into buttered casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Use 1 1/2-quart round Pyrex dish. Cook 30 minutes at 350° or until center is firm.

title: grandma sparrow's sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Set whites aside.
Cream sugar and butter. Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Alternate sour cream and flour with baking soda, mixed into flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: maple walnut bars
directions: Beat egg and add sugar and blend.
Add melted margarine, flour, flavorings, walnuts and raisins and blend until well mixed. Spread evenly in a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and then cut into squares with a sharp knife.
Yield:
16 generous squares.
These are good for shipping to someone for a gift.

title: italian love cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions on the box and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well the cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Spoon cheese mixture on top of unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: crab dip or spread
directions: Mix the cream cheese with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: easy peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper or cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Refrigerate.

title: cauliflower and pea salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut into small pieces.
Add green peas, cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well and add 1/2 to full package of dried dressing (depending on desired taste).
Chill in fridge. Makes 1 large mixing bowl full.

title: maple milk
directions: Dissolve the pudding mix in a little milk, blend everything together and enjoy.

title: 7 minute hamburger skillet
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off drippings. Blend in gravy mix, garlic salt, water and uncooked rice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in thawed peas and water chestnuts.
Simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in onions. Serve with soy sauce.

title: potpourri fruit cake
directions: Mix well and press into foil-lined loaf pan that has been oiled.
Bake at 300° fo 1 1/2 hours more or less, until done.

title: no-roll pastry
directions: Sift directly into a 9-inch pie pan the first 3 ingredients. Mix oil and milk in a cup.
Pour over the flour and mix with a fork until no dry flour shows.
Press with fingers to line pan and sides as evenly as possible.
Fill and bake according to recipe for any one-crust pie.

title: whole wheat-banana pancakes
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Combine milk and next three ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
(Start with 2/3 cup milk and add more if necessary after all ingredients are combined.)
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot nonstick griddle or nonstick skillet.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked. Makes approximately 9 (4 inch) pancakes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Blend milk, sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks, then add to main mixture.
Return to heat and cook 1 minute longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: glenda's butterscotch cookies
directions: Put flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in sifter.
Mix together shortening, oil, brown sugar, eggs and water.
Then add mixture together in sifter.
Mix up.
Add oatmeal and butterscotch.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Dilute mushroom soup with milk.
Add salt; mix well.
Peel and thinly slice potatoes and place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° until potatoes are tender.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Rinse kraut.
In saucepan, put bacon, apple, celery and carrot. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sauerkraut, vinegar, sugar, caraway seed, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook slowly until carrots are tender.

title: mrs. willey's waffles
directions: Sift flour; resift with baking powder and salt.
Separate egg yolks; add milk and oil to yolks and stir in flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar slowly and beat until smooth.
Fold in lightly, but thoroughly into batter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Melt butter or margarine to pour over cooked waffle.
Use syrup at room temperature.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, lemon juice, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in pan.
Cook over low heat until blueberries are soft (about 15 minutes).
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons of water in a small bowl; stir well and add to blueberry mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Set aside to cool.

title: spicy crab dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese and vodka; beat until smooth.
Stir in crab, cheese, onions, horseradish and pepper. Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Cream margarine and eggs (adding 1 at a time).
Add flour mixture, evaporated milk and flavorings alternately until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and let set at least 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: snow ice cream(wintertime fun for kids)
directions: Make sure snow is clean.
Make as little or as much as you like.
Add vanilla and sugar to taste.
Half and half is best; not too much or it gets soupy too fast.
Eat right away.
A dish of snow in the freezer keeps several days.

title: texas pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: cherry fruit bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie filling.
Spread 3/4 of batter into greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread pie filling on batter.
Dot remaining batter on top of pie filling and spread around a little.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar (sprinkle on) or powdered sugar/milk glaze.
Great served warm for breakfast or as a dessert.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together until spreadable consistency. Add package of salad dressing mix.
